#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:7
msgid "Advanced Email Management"
msgstr "Gestion avancée des emails"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:9
msgid ""
"This section delves into more advanced email management techniques that "
"offer significant long-term benefits. For |product| enthusiasts, we "
"strongly advise taking note of these strategies. Techniques include "
"effectively handling spam emails, utilizing email filters, and email "
"signatures, etc."
msgstr ""
"Cette section explore des techniques de gestion des e‑mails plus "
"avancées, offrant d’importants bénéfices à long terme. Pour les "
"passionnés de |product|, nous vous recommandons vivement de prendre en "
"compte ces stratégies. Les techniques comprennent la gestion efficace du "
"spam, l’utilisation de filtres e‑mail et de signatures, etc."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:12
msgid "Email Check Frequency"
msgstr "Fréquence de vérification des e‑mails"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:14
msgid ""
"You can customize how frequently you receive emails by adjusting your "
"settings. Here is how:"
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez personnaliser la fréquence de réception des e‑mails en "
"modifiant vos paramètres. Voici comment :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:16
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:49
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:110
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:125
msgid "Click on the Settings (gear icon) in the left sidebar."
msgstr "Cliquez sur Paramètres (icône engrenage) dans la barre latérale gauche."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:17
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:50
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:111
msgid "Select Mails."
msgstr "Sélectionnez Mails."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:18
msgid "Under Displaying Messages, click on Check new e-mail."
msgstr "Dans Affichage des messages, cliquez sur Vérifier les nouveaux e‑mails."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:19
msgid ""
"From the drop-down menu, choose how often you would like to check for new"
" mail."
msgstr ""
"Dans le menu déroulant, choisissez la fréquence de vérification des "
"nouveaux e‑mails."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:20
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:52
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:114
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:131
msgid "Click the SAVE button in the top right corner."
msgstr "Cliquez sur le bouton ENREGISTRER en haut à droite."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:22
msgid ""
"If you select Manually, you will need to click the reload icon to fetch "
"new emails. If you choose As new email arrives, your inbox will refresh "
"automatically upon receiving a new email."
msgstr ""
"Si vous choisissez Manuellement, vous devrez cliquer sur l’icône de "
"rechargement pour récupérer les nouveaux e‑mails. Si vous choisissez Dès "
"la réception d’un nouveau e‑mail, votre boîte de réception se rafraîchira"
" automatiquement à chaque arrivée."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:29
msgid "Email Notification"
msgstr "Notification d’e‑mail"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:31
msgid ""
"You can customize whether you are notified when you receive new emails. "
"To enable desktop alerts for new email notifications, ensure that your "
"web client is open on your browser."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez personnaliser la réception des notifications à la réception "
"de nouveaux e‑mails. Pour activer les alertes de bureau, assurez‑vous que"
" votre client web est ouvert dans le navigateur."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:33
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:145
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:158
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:202
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:261
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:300
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:315
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:328
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:339
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:369
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:391
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:402
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:415
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:451
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:504
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:519 ../../calendars/toc.rst:24
#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:140 ../../calendars/toc.rst:156
#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:167
msgid "Click on the **Settings** (gear icon) in the left sidebar."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur **Paramètres** (icône engrenage) dans la barre latérale "
"gauche."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:34
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:146
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:159
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:203
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:262
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:301
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:316
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:329
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:340
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:370
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:392
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:403
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:416
msgid "Select **Mails**."
msgstr "Sélectionnez **Mails**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:35
msgid ""
"Under **Arrival Notifications**, you will see different notification "
"options."
msgstr ""
"Dans **Notifications d’arrivée**, vous trouverez différentes options de "
"notification."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:36
msgid ""
"Check the box for **Show a popup notification** if you prefer a window "
"pop-up when receiving a new email."
msgstr ""
"Cochez **Afficher une notification popup** si vous préférez une fenêtre "
"pop‑up à la réception d’un nouveau e‑mail."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:37
msgid ""
"Check the box for the **Play audio hint when new notification appears** "
"if you prefer an audible notification for incoming emails."
msgstr ""
"Cochez **Émettre un son lors de l’apparition d’une nouvelle "
"notification** si vous souhaitez une alerte sonore pour les e‑mails "
"entrants."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:38
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:149
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:162
msgid "Click the **SAVE** button in the top right corner."
msgstr "Cliquez sur le bouton **ENREGISTRER** en haut à droite."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:45
msgid "Receiving Notifications via Another Email Address"
msgstr "Réception de notifications via une autre adresse e‑mail"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:47
msgid ""
"You can customize your email preferences to receive notifications at "
"another email address when you receive an email in your |product| inbox. "
"This option can be particularly beneficial if you do not receive a high "
"volume of emails to this account, but those you do receive require prompt"
" attention. Unlike the email notifications mentioned in the previous "
"section, for this feature, you do not need to keep your |product| webmail"
" open."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez configurer vos préférences e‑mail pour recevoir des "
"notifications à une autre adresse lorsqu’un e‑mail arrive dans votre "
"boîte |product|. Cette option est utile si vous recevez peu d’e‑mails sur"
" ce compte, mais que ceux‑ci nécessitent une action rapide. Contrairement"
" aux notifications décrites précédemment, aucune ouverture de votre "
"webmail |product| n’est requise pour cette fonction."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:51
msgid ""
"Under Message Arrival, insert another email address (e.g., your Gmail "
"address)."
msgstr ""
"Dans Arrivée des messages, saisissez une autre adresse e‑mail (par ex. "
"votre adresse Gmail)."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:54
msgid ""
"Going forward, you will receive an email notification on your Gmail "
"account whenever a new email arrives in your |product| inbox."
msgstr ""
"Désormais, vous recevrez une notification par e‑mail sur votre compte "
"Gmail chaque fois qu’un nouveau message arrive dans votre boîte de "
"réception |product|."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:61
msgid "Marking an Email as Spam"
msgstr "Marquer un e‑mail comme spam"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:63
msgid ""
"Most unsolicited automated emails, commonly referred to as spam or junk "
"mail, are filtered by a spam filter before they reach your Inbox. Emails "
"that are potentially junk but not definitively identified as such are "
"directed to your Junk folder. You have the option to review these "
"messages and either move them out of the Junk folder or delete them. If "
"left untouched, these messages are automatically removed after a certain "
"number of days, as determined by your system administrator. If you find "
"yourself inundated with a significant volume of unwanted emails, it is "
"advisable to reach out to your system administrator. Marking such emails "
"as spam automatically helps |product| in refining the spam filtering "
"process."
msgstr ""
"La plupart des e‑mails automatisés non sollicités, appelés spam ou "
"courrier indésirable, sont filtrés avant d’atteindre votre boîte de "
"réception. Les messages potentiellement indésirables mais non identifiés "
"avec certitude sont dirigés vers le dossier Courrier indésirable. Vous "
"pouvez examiner ces messages et les déplacer hors du dossier ou les "
"supprimer. S’ils ne sont pas traités, ils sont automatiquement supprimés "
"après un certain nombre de jours, selon les paramètres de "
"l’administrateur système. En cas de volume important de messages "
"indésirables, contactez votre administrateur système. Le fait de marquer "
"ces e‑mails comme spam aide automatiquement |product| à affiner le "
"filtrage."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:68
msgid "Right-click on the email you wish to mark as spam."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez avec le bouton droit sur l’e‑mail que vous souhaitez marquer "
"comme spam."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:69
msgid "From the menu that appears, select Mark as spam."
msgstr "Dans le menu qui s’affiche, choisissez Marquer comme spam."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:70
msgid "Your email will be automatically moved to your Junk Folder."
msgstr ""
"Votre e‑mail sera automatiquement déplacé vers votre dossier Courrier "
"indésirable."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:73
msgid "Removing Spam Emails"
msgstr "Suppression des e‑mails spam"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:75
msgid ""
"If you do not take action to remove your spam emails, they will be "
"automatically purged after a certain period, as determined by your system"
" administrator. To remove your spam emails:"
msgstr ""
"Si vous n’intervenez pas pour supprimer vos e‑mails spam, ils seront "
"automatiquement purgés après un certain délai, selon les paramètres de "
"l’administrateur système. Pour supprimer vos e‑mails spam :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:77
msgid "Click on the **Mails** in the left sidebar."
msgstr "Cliquez sur **Mails** dans la barre latérale gauche."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:78
msgid "Right-click on the **Junk** folder."
msgstr "Cliquez avec le bouton droit sur le dossier **Junk**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:79
msgid "Select **Wipe Folder** from the menu."
msgstr "Sélectionnez **Wipe Folder** dans le menu."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:81
msgid ""
"If you need to remove a specific spam email, you can easily right-click "
"on the email and select **Delete**."
msgstr ""
"Pour supprimer un e‑mail spam spécifique, cliquez simplement avec le "
"bouton droit sur l’e‑mail et choisissez **Delete**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:84
msgid "Marking Email as Not Spam"
msgstr "Marquer l’e‑mail comme non spam"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:86
msgid ""
"Occasionally, emails that are not junk may end up in the Junk folder. In "
"such cases, you can manually move these emails to the appropriate folder."
msgstr ""
"Il arrive que des e‑mails légitimes se retrouvent dans le dossier "
"Courrier indésirable. Dans ce cas, vous pouvez les déplacer manuellement "
"vers le dossier approprié."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:88
msgid "Go to your **Junk** folder."
msgstr "Accédez à votre dossier **Junk**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:89
msgid "Right-click on the email you wish to mark as not spam."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez avec le bouton droit sur l’e‑mail que vous souhaitez marquer "
"comme non spam."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:90
msgid "From the menu that appears, select **Not spam**."
msgstr "Dans le menu qui s’affiche, choisissez **Not spam**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:91
msgid "Your email will be automatically moved to the intended folder."
msgstr "Votre e‑mail sera automatiquement déplacé vers le dossier prévu."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:94
msgid "Finding the Origin of an Email"
msgstr "Déterminer l’origine d’un e‑mail"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:96
msgid ""
"The transportation history of emails serves various purposes, including "
"verifying authenticity, investigating delivery issues, detecting phishing"
" attempts, debugging email server configurations, ensuring compliance, "
"and fulfilling legal requirements. This information is typically "
"displayed on a text page, including the email header (also called "
"envelope information) and the email body. The email header contains vital"
" details about the email's journey, such as sender and recipient IP "
"addresses, timestamps, and any spam detection information."
msgstr ""
"L’historique de transport des e‑mails remplit plusieurs fonctions, "
"notamment la vérification d’authenticité, l’enquête sur les problèmes de "
"livraison, la détection de tentatives de phishing, le debug des "
"configurations de serveur mail, la conformité réglementaire et les "
"exigences légales. Ces informations sont généralement affichées sur une "
"page texte, comprenant l’en‑tête du mail (également appelée informations "
"d’enveloppe) et le corps du message. L’en‑tête du mail contient des "
"détails essentiels sur le trajet du message, tels que les adresses IP de "
"l’expéditeur et du destinataire, les horodatages et les informations de "
"détection de spam."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:98
msgid "To trace the email’s origin, follow these steps:"
msgstr "Pour tracer l'origine de l'e-mail, suivez ces étapes :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:100
#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:110
#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:123 ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:212
#: ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:232 ../../composing_emails/toc.rst:243
msgid "Right-click on the email."
msgstr "Cliquez avec le bouton droit sur l'e-mail."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:101
msgid "Select Show original."
msgstr "Sélectionnez Afficher l'original."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:102
msgid "A new window will open, displaying the relevant information."
msgstr "Une nouvelle fenêtre s'ouvrira, affichant les informations pertinentes."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:105
msgid "Setting Up Trusted Addresses"
msgstr "Configuration des adresses de confiance"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:107
msgid ""
"You have the option to designate email addresses from specific domains as"
" trusted addresses (the domain is part of the address after the @ like "
"the yourCompany in your.name@yourCompany.com. Doing so ensures that any "
"embedded images in emails received from addresses with this domain will "
"automatically display upon opening the email. Here is how to do it:"
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez désigner les adresses e‑mail provenant de domaines "
"spécifiques comme adresses de confiance (le domaine correspond à la "
"partie après le @, par ex. votreEntreprise dans "
"votre.nom@votreEntreprise.com). Ainsi, les images intégrées aux e‑mails "
"provenant de ce domaine s’afficheront automatiquement à l’ouverture. "
"Voici la procédure :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:112
msgid ""
"Under Trusted addresses, set email address, or domain name in the "
"provided text box. If you want to trust all addresses from a specific "
"domain, use the entire domain name."
msgstr ""
"Dans la section Adresses de confiance, saisissez l’adresse e‑mail ou le "
"nom de domaine dans le champ prévu. Pour faire confiance à toutes les "
"adresses d’un domaine, indiquez le domaine complet."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:113
msgid "Click the Add button to add the address or domain to the trusted list."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur le bouton Ajouter pour inscrire l’adresse ou le domaine dans "
"la liste de confiance."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:121
msgid "Creating an Out-of-Office Email"
msgstr "Création d’un message d’absence du bureau"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:123
msgid ""
"When you are away from the office, setting up an automatic reply can keep"
" colleagues and clients informed. Here is how to set it up:"
msgstr ""
"Lorsque vous êtes absent du bureau, configurer une réponse automatique "
"informe vos collègues et clients. Voici comment procéder :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:126 ../../get_started/toc.rst:229
#: ../../get_started/toc.rst:254 ../../get_started/toc.rst:288
msgid "Select General Settings."
msgstr "Sélectionnez Paramètres généraux."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:127
msgid ""
"Under Out of Office Settings, select Send auto-replies from the first "
"drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"Dans Paramètres d’absence, choisissez Envoyer des réponses automatiques "
"dans le premier menu déroulant."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:128
msgid ""
"In the Auto-Reply Message field, type the message you would like to be "
"sent out while you are away."
msgstr ""
"Dans le champ Message de réponse automatique, saisissez le texte à "
"envoyer pendant votre absence."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:129
msgid "Select the recipient from the External Senders field."
msgstr "Sélectionnez le destinataire dans le champ Expéditeurs externes."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:130
msgid ""
"Under Time Period select Send auto-replies during the following period "
"and select the dates."
msgstr ""
"Dans Période, choisissez Envoyer des réponses automatiques pendant la "
"période suivante et indiquez les dates."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:133
msgid ""
"If you prefer to send the out-of-office email only during specific hours "
"of the day, you can customize the interval by selecting All Day and then "
"specifying the desired time frame by choosing the start and end hours."
msgstr ""
"Si vous ne souhaitez envoyer le message d’absence que pendant des heures "
"précises, personnalisez l’intervalle en sélectionnant Toute la journée, "
"puis définissez l’horaire souhaité en choisissant les heures de début et "
"de fin."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:140
msgid "Showing Emails in HTML or Plain Text Format"
msgstr "Affichage des e‑mails au format HTML ou texte brut"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:142
msgid ""
"You can view email messages in two formats, HTML, or plain text. HTML "
"messages can have text formatting, numbering, bullets, colored "
"backgrounds, and links, which can make messages easier to read. Plain "
"text messages can always be read by other email clients. Plain text does "
"not support any text formatting, styles, links, or images. You can view a"
" message in plain-text mode even if it contains HTML. The HTML tags are "
"displayed in the body of the message in the plain text view."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez afficher les messages e‑mail au format HTML ou texte brut. "
"Les messages HTML permettent mise en forme, listes, puces, arrière‑plans "
"colorés et liens, facilitant la lecture. Les messages texte brut sont "
"lisibles par tous les clients e‑mail mais ne prennent en charge aucune "
"mise en forme, style, lien ou image. Vous pouvez afficher un message au "
"format texte même s’il contient du HTML ; les balises HTML sont alors "
"affichées dans le corps du message."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:147
msgid "Under Displaying Messages, click on the Display mail field."
msgstr "Dans Affichage des messages, cliquez sur le champ Afficher le courrier."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:148
msgid "From the drop-down menu, select **As HTML** or **As text**."
msgstr "Dans le menu déroulant, choisissez **En HTML** ou **En texte**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:152
msgid "Configuring Read Receipts Behavior"
msgstr "Configuration du comportement des accusés de lecture"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:154
msgid ""
"When sending messages to other |product| users, you can choose to request"
" a return receipt, which notifies you when the recipient opens your "
"email. However, for this feature to function, the recipient must have the"
" read receipt feature enabled or manually accept it as soon as they open "
"the email."
msgstr ""
"Lors de l'envoi de messages à d'autres utilisateurs |product|, vous "
"pouvez choisir de demander un accusé de réception, qui vous informe "
"lorsque le destinataire ouvre votre courriel. Toutefois, pour que cette "
"fonction fonctionne, le destinataire doit avoir l'accusé de lecture "
"activé ou l'accepter manuellement dès l'ouverture du courriel."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:156
msgid "To enable the read receipt feature:"
msgstr "Pour activer la fonction d'accusé de lecture :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:160
msgid "Under **Receiving Messages**, click on the **Read Receipt** field."
msgstr ""
"Dans **Réception des messages**, cliquez sur le champ **Accusé de "
"lecture**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:161
msgid "Select **Always send a read receipt**."
msgstr "Sélectionnez **Toujours envoyer un accusé de lecture**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:164
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can choose the option **Never send a read receipt** to"
" ensure it is never sent automatically or select **Ask me** so that you "
"are prompted each time you open an email with a read receipt request, "
"giving you the choice to send it or not."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez également choisir l'option **Ne jamais envoyer d'accusé de "
"lecture** pour empêcher tout envoi automatique, ou sélectionner **Me "
"demander** afin d'être invité à chaque ouverture d'un courriel contenant "
"une demande d'accusé de lecture, vous laissant le choix de l'envoyer ou "
"non."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:171
msgid "Setting Up Email Filters"
msgstr "Configuration des filtres de courriel"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:173
msgid ""
"You can effectively manage your inbox by utilizing email filters. These "
"filters allow you to set up actions, such as organizing incoming and "
"outgoing emails into specific folders."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez gérer efficacement votre boîte de réception en utilisant des "
"filtres de courriel. Ces filtres vous permettent de définir des actions, "
"comme organiser les courriels entrants et sortants dans des dossiers "
"spécifiques."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:175
msgid ""
"A filter consists of specific conditions paired with corresponding "
"actions."
msgstr ""
"Un filtre se compose de conditions spécifiques associées à des actions "
"correspondantes."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:177
msgid ""
"When an email satisfies the specified conditions, the designated actions "
"are triggered."
msgstr ""
"Lorsqu'un courriel répond aux conditions définies, les actions désignées "
"sont déclenchées."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:179
msgid ""
"Conditions can encompass various criteria, such as the subject, sender, "
"or date of the email."
msgstr ""
"Les conditions peuvent couvrir divers critères, tels que l'objet, "
"l'expéditeur ou la date du courriel."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:180
msgid "Actions may include moving, tagging, or redirecting the emails."
msgstr ""
"Les actions peuvent inclure le déplacement, le marquage ou le redirection"
" des courriels."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:182
msgid "Some examples are:"
msgstr "Voici quelques exemples :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:184
msgid ""
"Automatically moving incoming emails into designated folders. For "
"instance, emails from your supervisor can be automatically routed to your"
" \"Management Directives\" folder upon arrival."
msgstr ""
"Déplacement automatique des courriels entrants vers des dossiers "
"désignés. Par exemple, les courriels de votre supérieur peuvent être "
"automatiquement dirigés vers le dossier « Directives de gestion » dès "
"leur arrivée."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:185
msgid ""
"Tag specific emails for easy identification. For example, emails from the"
" corporate events mailing list can be labeled with an \"Events\" tag."
msgstr ""
"Marquage de courriels spécifiques pour une identification aisée. Par "
"exemple, les courriels de la liste de diffusion des événements "
"d'entreprise peuvent être étiquetés avec le tag « Événements »."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:186
msgid ""
"Redirect or delete emails based on predefined criteria. For instance, all"
" emails from a specific sender can be forwarded or moved to the Trash "
"folder."
msgstr ""
"Redirection ou suppression de courriels selon des critères prédéfinis. "
"Par exemple, tous les courriels d'un expéditeur donné peuvent être "
"transférés ou déplacés vers le dossier Corbeille."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:187
msgid "Assign importance flags to specific emails."
msgstr "Attribuer des indicateurs d'importance à des courriels spécifiques."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:189
msgid ""
"Filters are applied sequentially, following the order in which they are "
"listed in your settings. You retain the flexibility to modify the order "
"of filters as needed."
msgstr ""
"Les filtres sont appliqués séquentiellement, selon l'ordre dans lequel "
"ils figurent dans vos paramètres. Vous conservez la possibilité de "
"modifier cet ordre selon vos besoins."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:192
msgid "Creating a Filter"
msgstr "Création d'un filtre"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:198
msgid "You can configure filters independently for incoming and outgoing emails."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez configurer des filtres séparément pour les courriels entrants"
" et sortants."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:200
msgid "To create a filter for **incoming** or **outgoing emails**:"
msgstr "Créer un filtre pour les **e‑mails entrants** ou **sortants** :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:204
msgid ""
"Under **Filters**, choose either **Incoming Message Filters** or "
"**Outgoing Message Filters** depending on whether you intend to create a "
"filter for emails you receive or emails you send, respectively."
msgstr ""
"Dans **Filtres**, choisissez **Filtres de messages entrants** ou "
"**Filtres de messages sortants** selon que vous souhaitez créer un filtre"
" pour les e‑mails reçus ou envoyés, respectivement."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:205
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:264
msgid "Click **CREATE**. A new window appears."
msgstr "Cliquez sur **CRÉER**. Une nouvelle fenêtre apparaît."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:206
msgid ""
"Insert a name for your filter in the **Filter Name** field (e.g., junk "
"mail)"
msgstr ""
"Saisissez un nom pour votre filtre dans le champ **Nom du filtre** (ex. :"
" indésirables)."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:207
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:266
msgid ""
"Ensure to mark the **Active filter** checkbox so the filter becomes "
"operational immediately upon its creation."
msgstr ""
"Cochez la case **Filtre actif** afin que le filtre soit opérationnel "
"immédiatement après sa création."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:208
msgid ""
"Under the **Conditions** section, select the proper options for the logic"
" of your filter. Press the + button if you need to add more conditions "
"(please refer to the section below titled **How to create conditions** "
"for guidance on setting up the necessary criteria)."
msgstr ""
"Dans la section **Conditions**, choisissez les options appropriées pour "
"la logique de votre filtre. Appuyez sur le bouton + pour ajouter d’autres"
" conditions (voir la section ci‑dessous **Comment créer des conditions** "
"pour les critères requis)."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:209
msgid ""
"Under the **Actions** section, choose the appropriate action to be taken "
"if the filter conditions are met. Press the **+** button if you need to "
"add more actions (please refer to the section below titled **How to "
"create actions** for guidance on setting up the necessary criteria)."
msgstr ""
"Dans la section **Actions**, sélectionnez l’action à appliquer lorsque "
"les conditions du filtre sont satisfaites. Appuyez sur le bouton **+** "
"pour ajouter d’autres actions (voir la section ci‑dessous **Comment créer"
" des actions** pour les critères requis)."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:210
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:274
msgid ""
"Check or uncheck the **Do not process additional filters** checkbox to "
"determine whether this filter rule, when its conditions are met, will "
"prevent the execution of any other rules. Enabling this option means that"
" once this filter’s conditions are satisfied, the system will not "
"evaluate any other filters."
msgstr ""
"Cochez ou décochez la case **Ne pas traiter d’autres filtres** pour "
"décider si, lorsque les conditions sont remplies, cette règle empêche "
"l’exécution de toute autre règle. Activer cette option signifie qu’une "
"fois les conditions du filtre satisfaites, le système n’évaluera aucun "
"autre filtre."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:211 ../../chat/toc.rst:25
#: ../../files/toc.rst:45 ../../files/toc.rst:55 ../../tasks/toc.rst:26
msgid "Click **CREATE**."
msgstr "Cliquez sur **CRÉER**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:213
msgid ""
"You can locate your filter under **Active Filters**, indicating that it "
"is already operational and will be applied to incoming emails."
msgstr ""
"Vous trouverez votre filtre sous **Filtres actifs**, ce qui indique qu’il"
" est déjà opérationnel et sera appliqué aux e‑mails entrants."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:215
msgid ""
"If you did not select the **Active filter** on step 6, you will find the "
"filter under the **Available Filters**. To activate it, simply select it "
"and click **ADD**."
msgstr ""
"Si vous n’avez pas coché **Filtre actif** à l’étape 6, le filtre "
"apparaîtra sous **Filtres disponibles**. Pour l’activer, sélectionnez‑le "
"et cliquez sur **AJOUTER**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:217
msgid "How to create conditions:"
msgstr "Comment créer des conditions :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:219
msgid ""
"Under the **Conditions** section, you can configure various fields. These"
" fields determine the conditions that must be met for your email filter "
"to execute the specified action."
msgstr ""
"Dans la section **Conditions**, vous pouvez configurer différents champs."
" Ces champs définissent les conditions à remplir pour que votre filtre "
"d’e‑mail exécute l’action spécifiée."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:221
msgid ""
"**If field**: In this field, you can specify whether **Any** or **All** "
"conditions need to be matched for the filter rule to be executed."
msgstr ""
"**Champ Si** : dans ce champ, indiquez si **N’importe laquelle** ou "
"**Toutes** les conditions doivent être satisfaites pour que la règle du "
"filtre soit exécutée."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:223
msgid "**First field**: This field contains multiple values. i.e."
msgstr "**Premier champ** : ce champ accepte plusieurs valeurs, par ex."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:225
msgid "**From**: Specifies the sender's email address."
msgstr "**De** : adresse e‑mail de l’expéditeur."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:226
msgid "**To**: Specifies the recipient's email address."
msgstr "**À** : adresse e‑mail du destinataire."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:227
msgid "**Cc**: Specifies the email addresses listed in the \"Cc\" field."
msgstr "**Cc** : adresses e‑mail indiquées dans le champ « Cc »."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:228
msgid ""
"**To** or **Cc**: Specifies email addresses in either the \"To\" or "
"\"Cc\" fields."
msgstr "**À** ou **Cc** : adresses e‑mail présentes dans le champ « À » ou « Cc »."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:229
msgid "**Subject**: Specifies keywords or phrases found in the email subject."
msgstr "**Objet** : mots‑clé ou expressions présents dans l’objet de l’e‑mail."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:230
msgid ""
"**Message**: Specifies email properties, such as those involved in "
"conversations I've participated in."
msgstr ""
"**Message** : Spécifie les propriétés du courriel, telles que celles des "
"conversations auxquelles j’ai participé."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:231
msgid "**Size**: Specifies the size of the email in kilobytes."
msgstr "**Taille** : Spécifie la taille du courriel en kilo‑octets."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:232
msgid "**Date**: Specifies the date the email was sent or received."
msgstr "**Date** : Spécifie la date d’envoi ou de réception du courriel."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:233
msgid "**Body**: Specifies specific content within the email body."
msgstr "**Corps** : Spécifie un contenu précis dans le corps du courriel."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:234
msgid "**Attachment**: Specifies the presence or absence of attachments."
msgstr "**Pièce jointe** : Indique la présence ou l’absence de pièces jointes."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:235
msgid ""
"**Read Receipt**: Specifies whether a read receipt has been requested or "
"received."
msgstr ""
"**Accusé de lecture** : Indique si un accusé de lecture a été demandé ou "
"reçu."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:236
msgid ""
"**Address In**: Specifies specific addresses (e.g., sender, or recipient)"
" that exist in the contacts or frequent emails."
msgstr ""
"**Adresse dans** : Spécifie des adresses précises (expéditeur ou "
"destinataire) présentes dans les contacts ou les courriels fréquents."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:237
msgid ""
"**Calendar**: Specifies events or calendar-related information within the"
" email, such as whether the invitation has been replied to."
msgstr ""
"**Calendrier** : Spécifie les événements ou les informations liées au "
"calendrier dans le courriel, par ex. si l’invitation a reçu une réponse."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:238
msgid "**Social**: Specifies social media-related content within the email."
msgstr "**Social** : Spécifie le contenu lié aux réseaux sociaux dans le courriel."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:239
msgid "**Header Named**: Specifies a custom email header name."
msgstr "**En‑tête nommé** : Spécifie le nom d’un en‑tête de courriel personnalisé."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:241
msgid ""
"You can choose anything among these values and your next field values "
"will appear accordingly."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez choisir n’importe quelle valeur parmi celles‑ci et les champs"
" suivants s’afficheront en conséquence."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:243
msgid ""
"**Second field**: Depending on the value of the first field, you will get"
" to choose values for this field. Let me give you an example. If you "
"choose From as a value in the first field, then in this field you will "
"get the following values to choose. (i.e. Matches Exactly, Does Not Match"
" Exactly, Contains, Does Not Contain, Matches Wildcard Condition, Does "
"Not Match Wildcard Condition). But if you choose Size as a value in the "
"first field, then you will get Under, Not Under, Over, and Not Over as "
"selectable values in this field. Similarly, for all other values of the "
"first field, you will get a different set of values for this field."
msgstr ""
"**Deuxième champ** : En fonction de la valeur du premier champ, vous "
"choisissez les valeurs de ce champ. Exemple : si vous choisissez « From »"
" comme valeur du premier champ, les options suivantes seront proposées : "
"« Correspond exactement », « Ne correspond pas exactement », « Contient "
"», « Ne contient pas », « Correspond à un motif générique », « Ne "
"correspond pas à un motif générique ». Si vous choisissez « Size », les "
"options seront « Inférieur à », « Pas inférieur à », « Supérieur à », « "
"Pas supérieur à ». Chaque valeur du premier champ génère un jeu d’options"
" différent pour ce champ."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:245
msgid ""
"Depending on the First field and second field, you may get additional "
"fields with different values."
msgstr ""
"Selon les valeurs du premier et du deuxième champ, des champs "
"supplémentaires avec d’autres valeurs peuvent apparaître."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:247
msgid "How to create actions:"
msgstr "Comment créer des actions :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:249
msgid ""
"Under the Action section, you can configure various fields. These fields "
"determine the actions to be taken if the specified conditions are met. "
"Actions have a few paths to set such as:"
msgstr ""
"Dans la section Action, vous pouvez configurer plusieurs champs. Ces "
"champs déterminent les actions à exécuter lorsque les conditions "
"spécifiées sont remplies. Les actions offrent plusieurs options, telles "
"que :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:251
msgid "**Discard**: Moves the email into the Junk folder."
msgstr "**Supprimer** : Déplace le courriel dans le dossier Courrier indésirable."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:252
msgid "**Move Into Folder**: Transfers the email to a specified folder."
msgstr ""
"**Déplacer vers le dossier** : Transfère le courriel vers un dossier "
"spécifié."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:253
msgid "**Mark As**: Marks the email as read or flagged."
msgstr "**Marquer comme** : Marque le courriel comme lu ou signalé."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:254
msgid "**Tag With**: Assigns a tag to the email."
msgstr "**Étiqueter avec** : Attribue une étiquette au courriel."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:255
msgid ""
"**Redirect To Address**: Redirects the email to the specified email "
"address."
msgstr ""
"**Rediriger vers l’adresse** : Redirige le courriel vers l’adresse "
"spécifiée."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:257
msgid "Example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:259
msgid ""
"Let's implement a filter to automatically move incoming emails containing"
" the keywords 'Drug' and 'Violence' into the Trash folder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:263
msgid "Under Filters, choose **Incoming Message Filters**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:265
msgid ""
"Insert a name for your filter in the **Filter Name** field (e.g., drug "
"junk mail)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:267
msgid ""
"Under the **Conditions** section, select **Any**. We set it to match any "
"condition, meaning if either 'Drug' or 'Violence' is found in the email, "
"it will be moved to the junk folder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:268
msgid ""
"In the first field, select **Body**, in the second field, select "
"**Contains**, and lastly in the third field, write *Violence* to specify "
"that any email containing the word 'Violence' in its body should trigger "
"the filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:269
msgid "Click on the **+** button to add another condition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:270
msgid ""
"In the first field, select **Body**, in the second field, select "
"**Contains**, and lastly in the third field, write *Drug* to specify that"
" any email containing the word 'Drug' in its body should trigger the "
"filter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:271
msgid "Under the **Actions** section, choose **Move Into Folder**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:272
msgid "Click **BROWSE**, and a new window appears."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:273
msgid "Select your Trash folder and click **CHOOSE**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:275
msgid "Click CREATE."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:282
msgid "Activating/Deactivating a Filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:284
msgid ""
"When creating a filter, you have the option to mark the **Active filter**"
" checkbox. If selected, your filter will be placed in the Active Filters "
"section; otherwise, it will be listed under **Available Filters**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:286
msgid ""
"Active Filters are operational and will be applied to emails "
"automatically. Conversely, filters kept in the Available Filters section "
"are inactive but can be retained for future use. You have the flexibility"
" to move them into the Active Filters section whenever needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:288
msgid ""
"To move a filter from the Active Filters to the Available Filters, simply"
" select the filter you want to deactivate and click on the **REMOVE** "
"button. This action will transfer the filter to the Available Filters "
"section, where it will remain inactive until reactivated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:289
msgid ""
"To move a filter from the Available Filters to the Active Filters, simply"
" select the filter you want to activate and click on the **ADD** button. "
"This action will transfer the filter to the Available Filters section, "
"where it will remain active until deactivated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:292
msgid "Applying a Filter to Existing Emails"
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:294
msgid ""
"Active Filters are automatically applied to new emails, whereas for "
"managing existing emails, you may need to manually apply a filter. For "
"instance, you can create a filter to move all emails containing the word "
"'Violence' into the junk folder to tidy up your inbox."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:296
msgid ""
"This manual application allows you to organize existing emails according "
"to your preferences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:298
msgid "To apply a filter to existing emails, follow these steps:"
msgstr "Pour appliquer un filtre aux e‑mails existants, suivez ces étapes :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:302
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:341
msgid ""
"Under Filters, choose **Incoming Message Filters** or **Outgoing Message "
"Filters**, depending on where your filter is located."
msgstr ""
"Dans **Filtres**, choisissez **Incoming Message Filters** ou **Outgoing "
"Message Filters**, selon l’emplacement du filtre."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:303
msgid "Select the filter you want to apply from the list."
msgstr "Sélectionnez le filtre à appliquer dans la liste."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:304
msgid "Click **APPLY**. A new window will appear."
msgstr "Cliquez sur **APPLY**. Une nouvelle fenêtre s’affiche."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:305
msgid ""
"From the drop-down menu, select the folder you want the filter to be "
"applied to."
msgstr "Dans le menu déroulant, choisissez le dossier auquel appliquer le filtre."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:306
msgid "Click **APPLY** to confirm and execute the filter on existing emails."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur **APPLY** pour confirmer et exécuter le filtre sur les "
"e‑mails existants."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:308
msgid ""
"Note: To avoid server overload, the standard configuration prevents a "
"filter from being applied on a folder with more than 10.000 items."
msgstr ""
"Remarque : pour éviter une surcharge du serveur, la configuration "
"standard empêche l’application d’un filtre sur un dossier contenant plus "
"de 10 000 éléments."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:311
msgid "Editing a Filter"
msgstr "Modifier un filtre"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:313
msgid "To edit an existing filter, follow these steps:"
msgstr "Pour modifier un filtre existant, suivez ces étapes :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:317
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:330
msgid ""
"Under Filters, choose Incoming **Message Filters** or **Outgoing Message "
"Filters**, depending on where your filter is located."
msgstr ""
"Dans **Filtres**, choisissez **Incoming Message Filters** ou **Outgoing "
"Message Filters**, selon l’emplacement du filtre."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:318
msgid "Select the filter you want to edit from the list."
msgstr "Sélectionnez le filtre à modifier dans la liste."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:319
msgid "Click **EDIT**. A new window will appear."
msgstr "Cliquez sur **EDIT**. Une nouvelle fenêtre s’affiche."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:320
msgid ""
"Perform your edits, ensuring the filter is set up according to your "
"preferences."
msgstr ""
"Effectuez vos modifications, en veillant à ce que le filtre soit "
"configuré selon vos préférences."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:321
msgid "Click **SAVE** to confirm and apply the changes."
msgstr "Cliquez sur **SAVE** pour confirmer et appliquer les modifications."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:324
msgid "Deleting a Filter"
msgstr "Supprimer un filtre"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:326
msgid "To delete an existing filter, follow these steps:"
msgstr "Pour supprimer un filtre existant, suivez ces étapes :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:331
msgid "Select the filter you want to delete from the list."
msgstr "Sélectionnez le filtre à supprimer dans la liste."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:332
msgid ""
"Click **DELETE**. A new window will appear; click **DELETE** again to "
"confirm and remove the selected filter."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur **DELETE**. Une nouvelle fenêtre s’affiche ; cliquez de "
"nouveau sur **DELETE** pour confirmer et supprimer le filtre sélectionné."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:335
msgid "Change Filter Order"
msgstr "Modifier l’ordre des filtres"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:337
msgid ""
"The order of filters determines their application. You have the freedom "
"to adjust the order of filters at any point to influence their priority "
"in processing emails. To change the order:"
msgstr ""
"L’ordre des filtres détermine leur application. Vous pouvez modifier cet "
"ordre à tout moment pour influencer leur priorité dans le traitement des "
"e‑mails. Pour changer l’ordre :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:342
msgid "Select a filter whose order you want to modify."
msgstr "Sélectionnez le filtre dont vous souhaitez modifier l'ordre."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:343
msgid ""
"Click the downward or upward arrow to adjust the position of the selected"
" filter, thereby changing its order in the list."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur la flèche vers le bas ou vers le haut pour ajuster la "
"position du filtre sélectionné, modifiant ainsi son ordre dans la liste."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:346
msgid "Account Signatures"
msgstr "Signatures de compte"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:348
msgid ""
"Incorporating an automatic signature at the end of your emails is a "
"common practice. A signature typically comprises your name along with any"
" supplementary text. If you are utilizing a **rich text editor**, you "
"have the flexibility to format your signature, insert URLs for links, and"
" include graphics. It is also feasible to create multiple signatures to "
"suit various contexts. For instance, you might opt for a formal signature"
" tailored for correspondence with clients, while reserving an informal "
"one for communication with friends. Moreover, if you manage multiple "
"email identities, often referred to as personas, you can devise distinct "
"signatures and allocate them to specific addresses."
msgstr ""
"Incorporer une signature automatique à la fin de vos e‑mails est une "
"pratique courante. Une signature comprend généralement votre nom ainsi "
"que tout texte supplémentaire. Si vous utilisez un **rich text editor**, "
"vous pouvez mettre en forme votre signature, insérer des URL pour des "
"liens et ajouter des images. Il est également possible de créer plusieurs"
" signatures pour différents contextes. Par exemple, vous pouvez choisir "
"une signature formelle pour la correspondance avec les clients, et une "
"signature informelle pour les amis. De plus, si vous gérez plusieurs "
"identités de messagerie, souvent appelées personas, vous pouvez créer des"
" signatures distinctes et les affecter à des adresses spécifiques."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:352
msgid "Using Signatures"
msgstr "Utilisation des signatures"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:354
msgid ""
"To ensure that signatures appear in your email, you must switch to the "
"**rich text editor** while composing."
msgstr ""
"Pour que les signatures apparaissent dans votre e‑mail, vous devez "
"activer le **rich text editor** lors de la rédaction."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:356
msgid "Follow these steps to toggle the rich text editor on:"
msgstr "Suivez ces étapes pour activer le rich text editor :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:358
msgid ""
"Click on the **three vertical dots** located in the top-right corner of "
"the compose board."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur les **trois points verticaux** situés en haut à droite du "
"panneau de rédaction."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:359
msgid "Select **Enable rich text editor** from the menu that appears."
msgstr "Sélectionnez **Enable rich text editor** dans le menu qui s’affiche."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:361
msgid ""
"When a signature is set, it will be visible at the end of the email you "
"are composing. Additionally, you can effortlessly switch between "
"identities /personas by selecting them from the top-left corner of the "
"composing board, automatically applying the respective signatures "
"assigned to each identity/persona."
msgstr ""
"Lorsqu’une signature est définie, elle apparaît à la fin de l’e‑mail en "
"cours de rédaction. De plus, vous pouvez facilement basculer entre les "
"identités / personas en les sélectionnant dans le coin supérieur gauche "
"du panneau de rédaction, ce qui applique automatiquement les signatures "
"correspondantes à chaque identité/persona."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:365
msgid "Creating Signatures"
msgstr "Création de signatures"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:367
msgid "To create a signature:"
msgstr "Pour créer une signature :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:371
msgid "Under the **Signatures** section, click **ADD SIGNATURE**."
msgstr "Dans la section **Signatures**, cliquez sur **ADD SIGNATURE**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:372
msgid "Provide a name for the signature in the designated field."
msgstr "Saisissez un nom pour la signature dans le champ prévu."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:373
