#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:376
msgid ""
"Anything composed in this section will automatically append to the end of"
" your email as shown in the following example::"
msgstr ""
"Tout ce qui est rédigé dans cette section sera automatiquement ajouté à "
"la fin de votre e‑mail, comme illustré dans l’exemple suivant :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:387
msgid "Editing Signatures"
msgstr "Modification des signatures"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:389
msgid "To edit a signature:"
msgstr "Pour modifier une signature :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:393
msgid "Under the **Signatures** section, click on the signature you want to edit."
msgstr "Dans la section **Signatures**, cliquez sur la signature à modifier."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:394
msgid "Utilize the rich text editor on the right side to edit your signature."
msgstr ""
"Utilisez l'éditeur de texte enrichi à droite pour modifier votre "
"signature."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:398
msgid "Removing Signatures"
msgstr "Suppression des signatures"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:400
msgid "To remove a signature:"
msgstr "Pour supprimer une signature :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:404
msgid ""
"Under the **Signatures section**, click on the signature you want to "
"remove."
msgstr "Sous la **Signatures section**, cliquez sur la signature à supprimer."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:405
msgid ""
"Hover your mouse cursor over the signature name. A red button labeled "
"**DELETE** will appear. Click on it, and the signature will be removed."
msgstr ""
"Survolez le nom de la signature. Un bouton rouge **DELETE** apparaîtra. "
"Cliquez dessus pour supprimer la signature."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:409
msgid "Assign Different Signatures to Different Identities / Personas"
msgstr "Attribuer des signatures différentes à chaque identité/persona"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:411
msgid ""
"You can personalize each account persona or identity with a unique "
"signature. This ensures that when selecting an identity/persona while "
"composing an email, the appropriate signature is automatically applied."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez associer une signature unique à chaque persona ou identité de"
" compte. Ainsi, lors du choix d’une identité/persona pendant la rédaction"
" d’un courriel, la signature correspondante est appliquée "
"automatiquement."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:413
msgid "To assign each identity/persona a signature:"
msgstr "Pour attribuer une signature à chaque identité/persona :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:417
msgid ""
"In the Signatures Usage section, choose a signature for each "
"persona/identity from the dropdown menu provided."
msgstr ""
"Dans la **Signatures Usage section**, sélectionnez une signature pour "
"chaque persona/identité dans le menu déroulant."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:420
msgid ""
"You can effortlessly switch between identities/personas by selecting them"
" from the top-left corner of the composing board, automatically applying "
"the respective signatures assigned to each identity/persona."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez changer d’identité/persona en les sélectionnant dans le coin "
"supérieur gauche de l’éditeur, la signature assignée à chaque identité "
"étant appliquée automatiquement."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:423
msgid "Changing Signature While Composing An Email"
msgstr "Modification de la signature lors de la rédaction d’un courriel"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:425
msgid ""
"If you have set two or more signatures, you can easily switch between "
"them, while you are writing an email."
msgstr ""
"Si vous avez plusieurs signatures, vous pouvez facilement en changer "
"pendant la rédaction d’un courriel."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:427
msgid ""
"Just click on the **feather pen icon** on top of the composing tab and "
"choose the one you want to use, between the different options in the "
"list, based on the existing signatures. You can also choose *Do not use a"
" signature* option, if you want to completely remove the signature from "
"the current email."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur l’**feather pen icon** en haut de l’onglet de rédaction et "
"choisissez celle à utiliser parmi les options listées, en fonction des "
"signatures existantes. Vous pouvez également sélectionner l’option *Do "
"not use a signature* pour supprimer toute signature du courriel en cours."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:435
msgid "Email Delegations"
msgstr "Délégations d’envoi de courriels"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:437
msgid ""
"You can permit others to send emails on your behalf. When someone sends "
"an email on your behalf, the recipient sees both your name and the "
"sender's name. It is important to note that this is not the same as "
"sharing your entire inbox. The sender operates from their email account "
"when sending emails on your behalf, with your name selected from the From"
" field drop-down menu as the sender."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez autoriser d’autres personnes à envoyer des courriels en votre"
" nom. Le destinataire voit alors votre nom ainsi que celui de "
"l’expéditeur. Il ne s’agit pas d’un partage complet de votre boîte de "
"réception. L’expéditeur envoie depuis son propre compte, votre nom étant "
"choisi dans le menu déroulant du champ De."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:439
msgid ""
"Similarly, if you have been delegated permission to send emails on behalf"
" of someone else, you can do so with their email address as the sender. "
"In this case, the From address will display both your email address and "
"the person you are representing. When you have been given authorization "
"to send an email to that person, their email address appears in the menu,"
" without including your address in the email."
msgstr ""
"De même, si vous avez reçu l’autorisation d’envoyer des courriels au nom "
"d’une autre personne, vous pouvez le faire en utilisant son adresse comme"
" expéditeur. Dans ce cas, le champ De affichera votre adresse ainsi que "
"celle de la personne représentée. Lorsque vous êtes autorisé à envoyer un"
" courriel à cette personne, son adresse apparaît dans le menu, sans "
"inclure votre adresse."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:441
msgid ""
"Email delegation can be particularly useful in scenarios where you need "
"someone else to handle your email correspondence on your behalf, such as "
"when you are out of the office or managing multiple responsibilities. It "
"allows for efficient management of emails without the need for direct "
"access to your inbox, streamlining communication processes. This feature "
"is especially handy for executives, assistants, or team members who need "
"to act on behalf of others while maintaining clarity about the sender's "
"identity."
msgstr ""
"La délégation d’envoi de courriels est utile lorsqu’une tierce personne "
"doit gérer votre correspondance, par exemple en votre absence ou lors de "
"la gestion de multiples responsabilités. Elle permet de gérer les "
"courriels efficacement sans accéder directement à votre boîte, en "
"simplifiant les processus de communication. Cette fonction est "
"particulièrement pratique pour les cadres, assistants ou membres d’équipe"
" qui doivent agir au nom d’autrui tout en conservant la clarté de "
"l’identité de l’expéditeur."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:445
msgid "Delegating Others to Send Emails on Your Behalf"
msgstr "Autoriser d’autres personnes à envoyer des courriels en votre nom"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:447
msgid ""
"You can authorize others to send messages on your behalf. When they do "
"so, your name and email address appear as the sender, even though the "
"message is dispatched from the delegate's inbox."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez autoriser d’autres personnes à envoyer des messages en votre "
"nom. Leur nom apparaît alors comme expéditeur, même si le message est "
"envoyé depuis la boîte du délégué."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:449
msgid "To set this up:"
msgstr "Pour configurer cela :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:452
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:505
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:520
msgid "Select **Accounts**."
msgstr "Sélectionnez **Accounts**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:453
msgid "In the Delegates section, click **ADD DELEGATE**."
msgstr "Dans la section Délégués, cliquez sur **ADD DELEGATE**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:454
msgid ""
"Enter the email address of the person you are authorizing; this should be"
" an internal user's address like one of your colleagues."
msgstr ""
"Saisissez l’adresse e‑mail de la personne que vous autorisez ; il doit "
"s’agir d’une adresse interne, par exemple celle d’un collègue."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:455
msgid "Choose the permissions you wish to grant, and then click **OK**."
msgstr "Sélectionnez les autorisations à accorder, puis cliquez sur **OK**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:456
msgid ""
"Choose Save a copy of sent messages to my Sent folder from the list, if "
"you want to get a copy of the email sent by the delegate. Otherwise, you "
"can choose different options based on your preferences."
msgstr ""
"Sélectionnez **Save a copy of sent messages to my Sent folder** dans la "
"liste si vous souhaitez recevoir une copie des e‑mails envoyés par le "
"délégué. Sinon, choisissez une autre option selon vos préférences."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:459
msgid ""
"An email notification will be sent to the designated person, informing "
"them of their newly acquired delegate permissions."
msgstr ""
"Une notification par e‑mail sera envoyée à la personne désignée, "
"l’informant de ses nouvelles autorisations de délégué."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:466
msgid "Sending Email on Behalf of Someone Else"
msgstr "Envoi d’e‑mail au nom d’un tiers"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:468
msgid ""
"If you have been granted delegate permissions for another person, you can"
" send emails on their behalf. While composing an email, click on the top-"
"left corner where your account name is displayed. From there, you can "
"select your email address, as well as any other identities or personas "
"you may have, and the person you are representing. If you have been "
"permitted to send messages as that individual, their email address will "
"be available in the menu. When selected, your address will be omitted "
"from the email."
msgstr ""
"Si vous avez reçu des autorisations de délégué pour une autre personne, "
"vous pouvez envoyer des e‑mails en son nom. Lors de la rédaction, cliquez"
" dans le coin supérieur gauche où le nom de votre compte est affiché. "
"Vous pouvez alors choisir votre adresse e‑mail, ainsi que les autres "
"identités ou personas dont vous disposez, et la personne que vous "
"représentez. Si vous êtes autorisé à envoyer des messages en tant que "
"cette personne, son adresse e‑mail apparaîtra dans le menu. Une fois "
"sélectionnée, votre adresse sera omise de l’e‑mail."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:477
msgid "Account Personas"
msgstr "Personas de compte"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:479
msgid ""
"When sending emails, each email is associated with an email account. By "
"default, your primary identity is tied to your account name when setting "
"up your email account. However, you have the option to create additional "
"email identities known as personas, which can be used to manage different"
" types of emails."
msgstr ""
"Lors de l’envoi d’e‑mails, chaque message est lié à un compte e‑mail. Par"
" défaut, votre identité principale est associée au nom de votre compte "
"lors de la configuration. Vous pouvez toutefois créer des identités "
"e‑mail supplémentaires appelées personas, utiles pour gérer différents "
"types de courriels."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:481
msgid ""
"For instance, you might establish one persona for your sales "
"correspondence and another for personal emails."
msgstr ""
"Par exemple, vous pouvez créer un persona pour vos échanges commerciaux "
"et un autre pour vos e‑mails personnels."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:483
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:488
msgid ""
"If you have multiple personas or external accounts linked, you can choose"
" the specific persona you wish to utilize when sending an email."
msgstr ""
"Si vous avez plusieurs personas ou des comptes externes associés, vous "
"pouvez choisir le persona à utiliser lors de l’envoi d’un e‑mail."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:486
msgid "Using Personas"
msgstr "Utilisation des personas"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:490
msgid "You can send emails from different personas while composing a message."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez envoyer des e‑mails depuis différents personas lors de la "
"rédaction d’un message."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:492
msgid ""
"The recipient will see the username aligned with the selected persona as "
"the sender of the emails."
msgstr ""
"Le destinataire verra le nom d’utilisateur associé au persona sélectionné"
" comme expéditeur."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:494
msgid "To switch personas, follow these steps:"
msgstr "Pour changer de persona, procédez comme suit :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:496
msgid ""
"Click on your email address located at the **top left corner** of the "
"composing board when composing your email."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur votre adresse e‑mail située dans le **coin supérieur gauche**"
" de l’interface de rédaction."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:497
msgid "Choose your preferred persona from the menu."
msgstr "Sélectionnez le persona souhaité dans le menu."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:500
msgid "Creating Personas"
msgstr "Création de personas"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:502
msgid "To create a new persona alongside your default one:"
msgstr "Pour créer un nouveau persona en plus de celui par défaut :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:506
msgid "Under the Accounts list section, click **ADD PERSONA**."
msgstr "Dans la section Liste des comptes, cliquez sur **ADD PERSONA**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:507
msgid ""
"Under the **Persona Settings** section, choose a name for the added "
"persona."
msgstr ""
"Dans la section **Persona Settings**, choisissez un nom pour la persona "
"ajoutée."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:515
msgid "Removing Personas"
msgstr "Suppression des personas"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:517
msgid "To remove a persona:"
msgstr "Pour supprimer une persona :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:521
msgid "Under the Accounts list section, select the persona you wish to remove."
msgstr "Dans la section Liste des comptes, sélectionnez la persona à supprimer."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:522
msgid "Click **DELETE**, and then **DELETE PERMANENTLY** to confirm."
msgstr "Cliquez sur **DELETE**, puis sur **DELETE PERMANENTLY** pour confirmer."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:525
msgid "Set Disposal Policies for a Folder"
msgstr "Définir les politiques de disposition pour un dossier"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:527
msgid ""
"The email **disposal policy** dictates that emails residing in a "
"specified folder and surpassing the disposal threshold will undergo "
"automated cleanup and deletion without requiring manual intervention."
msgstr ""
"La **politique de disposition** des e‑mails indique que les e‑mails se "
"trouvant dans un dossier spécifié et dépassant le seuil de disposition "
"seront automatiquement nettoyés et supprimés sans intervention manuelle."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:529
msgid "To enable and set a **disposal policy** for a folder:"
msgstr "Pour activer et définir une **disposal policy** pour un dossier :"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:531
#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:22
#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:34
#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:64
msgid "From the left sidebar click on the **Mails** section."
msgstr "Dans la barre latérale gauche, cliquez sur la section **Mails**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:532
msgid ""
"In the Navigation Panel, right-click on the folder for which you wish to "
"set its disposal policy."
msgstr ""
"Dans le panneau de navigation, faites un clic droit sur le dossier dont "
"vous souhaitez définir la disposal policy."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:533
msgid "From the dropdown menu, select **Edit**. A new window appears."
msgstr ""
"Dans le menu déroulant, sélectionnez **Edit**. Une nouvelle fenêtre "
"s’affiche."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:534
msgid "Click the downward arrow next to the **Retention policy** section."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur la flèche vers le bas à côté de la section **Retention "
"policy**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:535
msgid "Tick the box labeled Enable Message Disposal."
msgstr "Cochez la case **Enable Message Disposal**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:536
msgid ""
"Enter a numerical value in the **Disposal Threshold** field and choose "
"the appropriate unit of time (such as days, weeks, etc.) from the "
"adjacent dropdown menu."
msgstr ""
"Saisissez une valeur numérique dans le champ **Disposal Threshold** et "
"choisissez l’unité de temps appropriée (jours, semaines, etc.) dans le "
"menu déroulant adjacent."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:537 ../../tasks/toc.rst:41
msgid "Click **EDIT**."
msgstr "Cliquez sur **EDIT**."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:539
msgid ""
"After clicking EDIT, the disposal policy will be applied to the specified"
" folder, triggering automated cleanup and deletion for emails surpassing "
"the disposal threshold."
msgstr ""
"Après avoir cliqué sur **EDIT**, la disposal policy est appliquée au "
"dossier spécifié, déclenchant le nettoyage et la suppression automatiques"
" des e‑mails dépassant le seuil de disposal."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:543
msgid "S/MIME signed emails"
msgstr "E‑mails signés S/MIME"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:545
msgid ""
"If you don't see these options, it means that your administrator has not "
"enabled them. Please contact your administrator for more information."
msgstr ""
"Si vous ne voyez pas ces options, cela signifie que votre administrateur "
"ne les a pas activées. Veuillez contacter votre administrateur pour plus "
"d’informations."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:547
msgid ""
"S/MIME (Secure/Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions) is a standard for "
"public key encryption and signing of MIME data. It is used to secure "
"email communications and is supported by most email clients. S/MIME "
"provides a way to encrypt email messages and digitally sign them. When "
"you digitally sign an email, you are adding a digital signature to the "
"message. This signature is unique to you and is used to verify that the "
"email has not been tampered with and that it was sent by you."
msgstr ""
"S/MIME (Secure/Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions) est une norme de "
"chiffrement à clé publique et de signature des données MIME. Elle est "
"utilisée pour sécuriser les communications par e‑mail et est prise en "
"charge par la plupart des clients de messagerie. S/MIME permet de "
"chiffrer les messages électroniques et de les signer numériquement. "
"Lorsque vous signez numériquement un e‑mail, vous ajoutez une signature "
"digitale au message. Cette signature, propre à vous, sert à vérifier que "
"l’e‑mail n’a pas été altéré et qu’il provient bien de vous."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:550
msgid "Difference between Signing and Encryption"
msgstr "Différence entre la signature et le chiffrement"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:552
msgid ""
"**Signing**: When you sign an email, you are adding a digital signature "
"to the message. This signature is unique to you and is used to verify "
"that the email has not been tampered with and that it was sent by you. "
"**Encryption**: When you encrypt an email, you are scrambling the "
"contents of the message so that only the intended recipient can read it. "
"This ensures that the email is secure and cannot be read by anyone else."
msgstr ""
"**Signing** : lorsque vous signez un e‑mail, vous ajoutez une signature "
"numérique au message. Cette signature est unique à vous et permet de "
"vérifier que l’e‑mail n’a pas été altéré et qu’il a été envoyé par vous. "
"**Encryption** : lorsque vous chiffrez un e‑mail, vous encodez le contenu"
" du message afin que seul le destinataire prévu puisse le lire. Cela "
"garantit la sécurité de l’e‑mail et empêche toute lecture par d’autres."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:556
msgid "Requirements for S/MIME"
msgstr "Requirements for S/MIME"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:558
msgid "To use S/MIME, you need:"
msgstr "To use S/MIME, you need:"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:560
msgid ""
"A valid S/MIME certificate (X.509 format) issued by a trusted Certificate"
" Authority (CA)."
msgstr ""
"A valid S/MIME certificate (X.509 format) issued by a trusted Certificate"
" Authority (CA)."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:561
msgid ""
"Carbonio webmail (S/MIME is not available in Carbonio Community Edition, "
"it only allows to show that the email is digitally signed)."
msgstr ""
"Carbonio webmail (S/MIME is not available in Carbonio Community Edition, "
"it only allows to show that the email is digitally signed)."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:562
msgid ""
"A compatible email client (Another user with Carbonio webmail, Outlook,  "
"Thunderbird --to check--,  others?)."
msgstr ""
"A compatible email client (Another user with Carbonio webmail, Outlook,  "
"Thunderbird --to check--,  others?)."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:565
msgid "Obtaining an S/MIME Certificate"
msgstr "Obtaining an S/MIME Certificate"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:567
msgid ""
"You need an S/MIME certificate issued by a trusted Certificate Authority "
"(CA).Popular CAs include: Sectigo (Comodo); DigiCert; GlobalSign; "
"Actalis; Entrust; GoDaddy; Thawte; VeriSign; and others."
msgstr ""
"You need an S/MIME certificate issued by a trusted Certificate Authority "
"(CA).Popular CAs include: Sectigo (Comodo); DigiCert; GlobalSign; "
"Actalis; Entrust; GoDaddy; Thawte; VeriSign; and others."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:569
msgid ""
"To obtain an S/MIME certificate: 1. Go to the website of a trusted CA. 2."
" Request an S/MIME certificate from a CA. 3. Download the certificate in "
"PKCS#12 format (.p12 or .pfx). 4. Note the password used to export the "
"private key."
msgstr ""
"To obtain an S/MIME certificate: 1. Go to the website of a trusted CA. 2."
" Request an S/MIME certificate from a CA. 3. Download the certificate in "
"PKCS#12 format (.p12 or .pfx). 4. Note the password used to export the "
"private key."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:576
msgid "How S/MIME Signing Works in Carbonio"
msgstr "How S/MIME Signing Works in Carbonio"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:579
msgid "Importing an S/MIME Certificate"
msgstr "Importing an S/MIME Certificate"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:581
msgid ""
"Upload your personal certificate (containing a public and a private key) "
"into Carbonio webmail via Settings → S/MIME Certificates (the system will"
" ask to enter a password to protect the certificate. If one has already "
"been set it will ask for the password)."
msgstr ""
"# Upload your personal certificate (containing a public and a private "
"key) into Carbonio webmail via Settings → S/MIME Certificates (the system"
" will ask to enter a password to protect the certificate. If one has "
"already been set it will ask for the password). # Click Upload "
"Certificate under Personal certificates for signing, encryption and "
"decryption."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:582
msgid ""
"Click Upload Certificate under Personal certificates for signing, "
"encryption and decryption."
msgstr ""
"Click \"Upload Certificate\" under Personal certificates for signing, "
"encryption and decryption."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:586
msgid "Signing an Email"
msgstr "Signing an Email"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:588
msgid "When composing an email, select \"Use certificate to sign (S/MIME)\"."
msgstr "Sélectionnez « Use certificate to encrypt (S/MIME) » avant d’envoyer."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:590
msgid "Carbonio uses the user's private key to generate a digital signature."
msgstr ""
"Carbonio utilise la clé privée de l'utilisateur pour générer une "
"signature numérique."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:591
msgid "The signature is attached to the email as a cryptographic hash."
msgstr "La signature est jointe au courriel sous forme de hachage cryptographique."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:592
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:602
msgid "The recipient can verify the signature using the sender's public key."
msgstr ""
"Le destinataire peut vérifier la signature à l'aide de la clé publique de"
" l'expéditeur."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:596
msgid "Verifying a Signed Email"
msgstr "Verifying a Signed Email"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:598
msgid ""
"When you receive a signed email, the signature is displayed in the email "
"header."
msgstr ""
"Lors de la réception d'un courriel signé, la signature apparaît dans l"
"’en-tête du courriel."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:600
msgid "Click on the signature to view the certificate details."
msgstr "Cliquez sur les trois points verticaux."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:601
msgid ""
"The certificate details include the certificate issuer, the certificate "
"validity period, and the certificate fingerprint."
msgstr ""
"Les détails du certificat comprennent l'émetteur du certificat, sa "
"période de validité et son empreinte."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:604
msgid "If the signature is valid:"
msgstr "If the signature is valid:"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:606
msgid "The recipient sees a signed email notification."
msgstr "The recipient sees a signed email notification."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:607
msgid ""
"It confirms the email hasn't been modified and is truly from the claimed "
"sender."
msgstr ""
"It confirms the email hasn’t been modified and is truly from the claimed "
"sender."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:609
msgid "If the signature is invalid or missing:"
msgstr "If the signature is valid:"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:611
msgid "The email might be tampered with or sent from an untrusted source."
msgstr "Le courriel peut avoir été altéré ou provenir d'une source non fiable."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:612
msgid "The recipient should be cautious when interacting with such emails."
msgstr ""
"Le destinataire doit rester prudent lorsqu'il interagit avec de tels "
"courriels."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:616
msgid "How S/MIME Encryption Works in Carbonio"
msgstr "How S/MIME Encryption Works in Carbonio"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:619
msgid "Key Components"
msgstr "Key Components"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:621
msgid ""
"**Public Key**: Used to encrypt the email. Stored in the recipient's "
"S/MIME certificate."
msgstr ""
"**Clé publique** : utilisée pour chiffrer le courriel. Stockée dans le "
"certificat S/MIME du destinataire."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:622
msgid ""
"**Private Key**: Used to decrypt the email. Stored securely by the "
"recipient."
msgstr ""
"**Clé privée** : utilisée pour déchiffrer le courriel. Stockée de façon "
"sécurisée par le destinataire."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:623
msgid "**Certificate Authority (CA)**: Issues S/MIME certificates to users."
msgstr ""
"**Autorité de certification (CA)** : délivre les certificats S/MIME aux "
"utilisateurs."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:626
msgid "The Encryption Process"
msgstr "The Encryption Process"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:628
msgid "Sender Retrieves Recipient's Public Key"
msgstr "Sender Retrieves Recipient’s Public Key"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:630
msgid "The sender must have the recipient's public key."
msgstr "The sender must have the recipient’s public key."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:632
msgid "Email Encryption"
msgstr "Email Encryption"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:634
msgid "The sender composes an email and selects  \"Encrypt with S/MIME\""
msgstr "The sender composes an email and selects  \"Encrypt with S/MIME\""

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:635
msgid "Sender email content is encrypted using the recipient's public key."
msgstr "Sender email content is encrypted using the recipient’s public key."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:636
msgid "The email is sent in an encrypted format."
msgstr "The email is sent in an encrypted format."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:637
msgid "Recipient Decrypts the Email"
msgstr "Réception et déchiffrement d’un e‑mail"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:639
msgid ""
"When the recipient opens the email, its private key is used to decrypt "
"the message."
msgstr ""
"Lorsque le destinataire ouvre le courriel, sa clé privée est utilisée "
"pour déchiffrer le message."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:640
msgid ""
"If the private key matches the encrypted data, the email is decrypted and"
" displayed normally."
msgstr ""
"Recipient Decrypts the Email * When the recipient opens the email, its "
"private key is used to decrypt the message. * If the private key matches "
"the encrypted data, the email is decrypted and displayed normally."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:642
msgid ""
"The recipient can only decrypt the email if they have the corresponding "
"private key. This ensures that only the intended recipient can read the "
"email."
msgstr ""
"The recipient can only decrypt the email if they have the corresponding "
"private key. This ensures that only the intended recipient can read the "
"email."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:645
msgid "Requirements for S/MIME Encryption"
msgstr "Requirements for S/MIME Encryption"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:647
msgid "Both sender and recipient must have S/MIME certificates installed."
msgstr ""
"# Both sender and recipient must have S/MIME certificates installed. # "
"The recipient’s public key must be available to the sender."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:648
msgid "The recipient's public key must be available to the sender."
msgstr ""
"# Both sender and recipient must have S/MIME certificates installed. # "
"The recipient’s public key must be available to the sender."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:651
msgid "Uploading a Certificate in Carbonio Webmail"
msgstr "Uploading a Certificate in Carbonio Webmail"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:653
msgid "Go to Settings → S/MIME Certificates."
msgstr "Go to Settings → S/MIME Certificates."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:654
msgid ""
"Click \"Upload Certificate\" under Personal certificates for signing, "
"encryption and decryption."
msgstr ""
"Click \"Upload Certificate\" under Personal certificates for signing, "
"encryption and decryption."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:655
msgid "Select your PKCS#12 certificate file (.pfx or .p12)."
msgstr "Select your PKCS#12 certificate file (.pfx or .p12)."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:656
msgid "Enter the certificate secret."
msgstr "Enter the certificate secret."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:657
#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:663
msgid "Click Save."
msgstr "Click Save."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:660
msgid "Uploading Recipient Certificate"
msgstr "Uploading Recipient Certificate"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:662
msgid "Click \"Upload Certificate\" under Recipients certificates for encryption"
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur « Upload Certificate » sous les certificats des destinataires"
" pour le chiffrement"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:666
msgid "Sending an Encrypted Email"
msgstr "Envoi d’un e‑mail chiffré"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:668
msgid "Compose a new email in Carbonio webmail."
msgstr "Rédigez un nouvel e‑mail dans le webmail Carbonio."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:669
msgid "Select \"Use certificate to encrypt (S/MIME)\" before sending."
msgstr "Sélectionnez « Use certificate to encrypt (S/MIME) » avant d’envoyer."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:670
msgid "The email will be encrypted using the recipient's public key."
msgstr "L’e‑mail sera chiffré avec la clé publique du destinataire."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:673
msgid "Receiving and Decrypting an Email"
msgstr "Réception et déchiffrement d’un e‑mail"

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:675
msgid ""
"If your private key is installed, Carbonio will automatically decrypt the"
" message."
msgstr ""
"Si votre clé privée est installée, Carbonio déchiffrera automatiquement "
"le message."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:676
msgid "If not, you'll see an \"Unable to decrypt\" error."
msgstr ""
"Dans le cas contraire, une erreur « Impossible de déchiffrer » "
"s'affichera."

#: ../../advanced_email_management/toc.rst:677
msgid "You can upload your private key to decrypt the message."
msgstr "Vous pouvez télécharger votre clé privée pour déchiffrer le message."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:7
msgid "Working with Appointments"
msgstr "Gestion des rendez‑vous"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:9
msgid ""
"Appointments serve as pivotal tools for organizing schedules, enabling "
"the creation of both one-time and recurring events, meetings, and "
"engagements."
msgstr ""
"Les rendez‑vous sont des outils essentiels pour organiser les plannings, "
"permettant la création d’événements ponctuels ou récurrents, de réunions "
"et d’engagements."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:11
msgid ""
"This feature facilitates efficient planning by allowing users to check "
"the availability of attendees before extending invitations, reserve "
"necessary resources such as meeting rooms and equipment, and append "
"personalized messages to invitations."
msgstr ""
"Cette fonction facilite la planification efficace en permettant aux "
"utilisateurs de vérifier la disponibilité des participants avant "
"d’envoyer des invitations, de réserver les ressources nécessaires (salles"
" de réunion, équipements) et d’ajouter des messages personnalisés aux "
"invitations."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:13
msgid ""
"Such features enhance communication and coordination, fostering a "
"productive work environment where employees can effectively manage their "
"time and collaborate seamlessly."
msgstr ""
"Ces fonctionnalités améliorent la communication et la coordination, "
"favorisant un environnement de travail productif où les employés gèrent "
"efficacement leur temps et collaborent sans friction."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:17
msgid "Creating an Appointment"
msgstr "Création d’un rendez‑vous"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:23
msgid "To create a new appointment:"
msgstr "Pour créer un nouveau rendez‑vous :"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:25 ../../appointments/toc.rst:81
#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:92 ../../appointments/toc.rst:103
#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:117 ../../appointments/toc.rst:128
#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:139 ../../appointments/toc.rst:154
#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:177 ../../appointments/toc.rst:190
#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:42 ../../calendars/toc.rst:61
#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:92 ../../calendars/toc.rst:103
#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:115 ../../calendars/toc.rst:127
#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:436 ../../calendars/toc.rst:472
#: ../../calendars/toc.rst:483 ../../calendars/toc.rst:496
msgid "Select the **Calendars** from your left sidebar."
msgstr "Sélectionnez **Calendars** dans la barre latérale gauche."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:26 ../../appointments/toc.rst:155
#: ../../tasks/toc.rst:21
msgid ""
"Click on the **NEW** button located on the top bar. A new board will "
"appear."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur le bouton **NEW** situé dans la barre supérieure. Un nouveau "
"tableau apparaît."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:27
msgid ""
"In the **From** field, select the identity you want to use to schedule "
"and send the appointment invitation."
msgstr ""
"Dans le champ **From**, choisissez l’identité à utiliser pour planifier "
"et envoyer l’invitation du rendez‑vous."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:28
msgid "Enter a title for the appointment in the **Event title** field."
msgstr "Saisissez un titre pour le rendez‑vous dans le champ **Event title**."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:29 ../../appointments/toc.rst:158
msgid ""
"Specify a location for the appointment to occur in the **Location "
"field**. If applicable, you may include details such as Room Number 2."
msgstr ""
"Indiquez le lieu du rendez‑vous dans le champ **Location**. Le cas "
"échéant, ajoutez des précisions comme « Room Number 2 »."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:30
msgid ""
"Choose a meeting room from the available options in the **Meeting room** "
"field. Please note that these meeting rooms are configured by your system"
" administrator. If you do not see the desired room listed, kindly contact"
" your system administrator to ensure all relevant meeting rooms in your "
"office are included."
msgstr ""
"Sélectionnez une salle de réunion parmi les options disponibles dans le "
"champ **Meeting room**. Ces salles sont configurées par votre "
"administrateur système. Si la salle souhaitée n’apparaît pas, contactez "
"votre administrateur pour qu’elle soit ajoutée."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:31
msgid ""
"If you prefer to host a virtual meeting using |product| Chats' video "
"meeting feature in one of your virtual rooms, you can select the desired "
"virtual room from the **Virtual Room field**. If you have not set up any "
"virtual rooms yet, you can easily create them by clicking the button "
"**\"CREATE NEW VIRTUAL ROOM\"**."
msgstr ""
"Si vous préférez organiser une réunion virtuelle en utilisant la fonction"
" de visioconférence de |product| Chats dans l’une de vos salles "
"virtuelles, sélectionnez la salle souhaitée dans le **champ Virtual "
"Room**. Si vous n’avez pas encore créé de salles virtuelles, vous pouvez "
"les créer facilement en cliquant sur le bouton **« CREATE NEW VIRTUAL "
"ROOM »**."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:32 ../../appointments/toc.rst:162
msgid ""
"Enter the email addresses of the attendees into the **Attendees field**. "
"You can leave this field empty if you are creating a personal appointment"
" for yourself."
msgstr ""
"Saisissez les adresses e‑mail des participants dans le **champ "
"Attendees**. Vous pouvez laisser ce champ vide si vous créez un "
"rendez‑vous personnel."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:33 ../../appointments/toc.rst:163
msgid ""
"Choose whether you would like |product| to mark this time slot for the "
"appointment as busy or free from the **Display field**. This will inform "
"your colleagues of your availability when they attempt to schedule "
"another appointment during the same time slot."
msgstr ""
"Choisissez si vous souhaitez que |product| indique ce créneau comme "
"occupé ou libre dans le **champ Display**. Cela informera vos collègues "
"de votre disponibilité lorsqu’ils essaieront de planifier un autre "
"rendez‑vous sur le même créneau."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:34 ../../appointments/toc.rst:164
msgid ""
"Choose the calendar in which you want to create the appointment from the "
"**Calendar field**."
msgstr ""
"Sélectionnez le calendrier dans lequel créer le rendez‑vous dans le "
"**champ Calendar**."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:35 ../../appointments/toc.rst:165
msgid ""
"Tick the **Private checkbox** if you wish to conceal the details of this "
"appointment, such as its title, from your colleagues. Even if you have "
"shared your calendar with them, your colleagues will still see the "
"appointment listed on your calendar, but without the specific details "
"like the title."
msgstr ""
"Cochez la **case Private** si vous souhaitez masquer les détails de ce "
"rendez‑vous (titre, etc.) à vos collègues. Même si vous avez partagé "
"votre calendrier, ils verront le rendez‑vous dans leur agenda, mais sans "
"les informations spécifiques comme le titre."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:36
msgid ""
"Choose the time slot for the appointment by specifying the start date and"
" time in the **Start date and time field**, and the end date and time in "
"the **End date and time field**. Alternatively, you can tick the checkbox"
" labeled **All day** if the appointment spans the entire day."
msgstr ""
"Définissez le créneau du rendez‑vous en indiquant la date et l’heure de "
"début dans le **champ Start date and time**, et la date et l’heure de fin"
" dans le **champ End date and time**. Vous pouvez également cocher la "
"case **All day** si le rendez‑vous dure toute la journée."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:37 ../../appointments/toc.rst:167
msgid ""
"Choose a reminder for the appointment from the **Reminder field** to "
"ensure you are informed beforehand. |product| will display a warning "
"window in the |product| client at the specified time to remind you of the"
" appointment."
msgstr ""
"Sélectionnez un rappel pour le rendez‑vous dans le **champ Reminder** "
"afin d’être prévenu à l’avance. |product| affichera une fenêtre "
"d’avertissement dans le client |product| à l’heure spécifiée pour vous "
"rappeler le rendez‑vous."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:38
msgid ""
"Tick the **repeat** recurrence of the appointment if you want to use any "
"of the pre-defined recurrences (every day, week, month, or year) or "
"define a custom one, that may end after a date or a number of "
"occurrences."
msgstr ""
"Cochez la récurrence **repeat** du rendez‑vous si vous souhaitez utiliser"
" l’une des récurrences prédéfinies (quotidienne, hebdomadaire, mensuelle "
"ou annuelle) ou en définir une personnalisée, pouvant se terminer à une "
"date ou après un nombre d’occurrences."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:39
msgid ""
"Choose the time zone, if different from the default one. You need to "
"enable this option in the Calendar's module settings, in *Creating "
"Appointment* Section."
msgstr ""
"Sélectionnez le fuseau horaire, s’il diffère de celui par défaut. Cette "
"option doit être activée dans les paramètres du module du calendrier, "
"section *Creating Appointment*."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:40 ../../appointments/toc.rst:168
msgid "Add any notes about this appointment in the text box."
msgstr "Ajoutez des notes concernant ce rendez‑vous dans la zone de texte."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:41 ../../appointments/toc.rst:170
msgid ""
"If you are creating the appointment solely for yourself, click **SAVE**. "
"If your appointment includes attendees, as specified in step 8, click "
"**SEND** to notify them via an automatic email."
msgstr ""
"Si vous créez le rendez‑vous uniquement pour vous, cliquez sur **SAVE**. "
"Si le rendez‑vous comporte des participants, comme indiqué à l’étape 8, "
"cliquez sur **SEND** pour les notifier par e‑mail automatique."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:44
msgid "How Equipment Resources work"
msgstr "Fonctionnement des ressources d’équipement"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:46
msgid ""
"Equipment resources (such as projectors, cameras, displays, company "
"laptops, etc.) are managed centrally by your system administrator. Each "
"piece of equipment is represented in Carbonio as a resource account that "
"can be added to appointments, similar to a meeting room."
msgstr ""
"Les ressources d’équipement (projecteurs, caméras, écrans, ordinateurs "
"portables de l’entreprise, etc.) sont gérées centralement par votre "
"administrateur système. Chaque équipement est représenté dans Carbonio "
"comme un compte ressource pouvant être ajouté aux rendez‑vous, à l’image "
"d’une salle de réunion."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:49
msgid "Assigning Equipment to an Appointment"
msgstr "Attribuer un équipement à un rendez‑vous"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:51
msgid ""
"When creating an appointment, users can choose one or more equipment "
"resources from the Equipment field (if enabled and configured by the "
"system administrator). Selecting equipment means that the resource is "
"reserved for the duration of the appointment, preventing overlapping "
"bookings. If a specific piece of equipment does not appear in the list, "
"users must contact their system administrator so it can be added as a "
"resource."
msgstr ""
"Lors de la création d’un rendez‑vous, les utilisateurs peuvent choisir "
"une ou plusieurs ressources d’équipement dans le champ Equipment (si "
"activé et configuré par l’administrateur système). Sélectionner un "
"équipement réserve la ressource pendant la durée du rendez‑vous, évitant "
"les conflits de réservation. Si un équipement spécifique n’apparaît pas "
"dans la liste, les utilisateurs doivent contacter leur administrateur "
"système pour qu’il soit ajouté en tant que ressource."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:55
msgid "Approval workflow for Equipment Requests"
msgstr "Flux d’approbation des demandes d’équipement"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:57
msgid "Equipment resources can operate in multiple modes:"
msgstr "Les ressources d'équipement peuvent fonctionner en plusieurs modes :"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:59
msgid ""
"**Auto-accept enabled**: the resource automatically accepts the booking "
"if it is available."
msgstr ""
"**Auto-accept enabled** : la ressource accepte automatiquement la "
"réservation si elle est disponible."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:60
msgid ""
"**Auto-accept disabled**: the resource does not automatically accept "
"requests."
msgstr ""
"**Auto-accept disabled** : la ressource n’accepte pas automatiquement les"
" demandes."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:61
msgid ""
"**Booking disabled**: the administrator can prevent any scheduled booking"
" for the equipment resource, including the ability to create recurring "
"appointments for that resource."
msgstr ""
"**Booking disabled** : l’administrateur peut empêcher toute réservation "
"planifiée de la ressource d’équipement, y compris la création de "
"rendez‑vous récurrents pour cette ressource."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:64
msgid ""
"When auto-acceptance is disabled, the system administrator can configure "
"the resource to forward booking requests to one or more designated users."
" These users act as **approvers** and can manually accept or decline each"
" equipment request. Their decision determines whether the equipment is "
"reserved for the appointment."
msgstr ""
"Lorsque l’auto‑acceptation est désactivée, l’administrateur système peut "
"configurer la ressource pour transmettre les demandes de réservation à un"
" ou plusieurs utilisateurs désignés. Ces utilisateurs agissent en tant "
"que **approvers** et peuvent accepter ou refuser manuellement chaque "
"demande d’équipement. Leur décision détermine si l’équipement est réservé"
" pour le rendez‑vous."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:70
msgid "Checking on attendees' availability with organizer tool"
msgstr "Vérification de la disponibilité des participants avec l’outil organizer"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:72
msgid ""
"When scheduling a new meeting, with expected other attendees, you will "
"also have the option to check on other attendees availability by simply "
"opening the **organizer tool**. Once you open the editor to create the "
"appointment, after selecting all participants (both mandatory and "
"optional), simply scroll down and click the “Show organizer tool” button."
" A new section will open, displaying a timeline chart for the selected "
"time range, showing the availability of each participant in the meeting. "
"This will make it easier to select the most convenient time for everyone."
" This section is particularly useful when there are many participants, "
"eliminating the need to check each individual calendar before choosing "
"the time."
msgstr ""
"Lors de la planification d’une nouvelle réunion avec d’autres "
"participants prévus, vous pouvez vérifier leur disponibilité en ouvrant "
"simplement l’**organizer tool**. Après avoir ouvert l’éditeur pour créer "
"le rendez‑vous et sélectionné tous les participants (obligatoires et "
"optionnels), faites défiler la page et cliquez sur le bouton « Show "
"organizer tool ». Une nouvelle section s’affiche, présentant un diagramme"
" chronologique de la plage horaire sélectionnée, indiquant la "
"disponibilité de chaque participant. Cela facilite la sélection du "
"créneau le plus adéquat pour tous. Cette section est particulièrement "
"utile lorsqu’il y a de nombreux participants, évitant de consulter chaque"
" calendrier individuellement avant de choisir l’horaire."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:77
msgid "Editing an Existing Appointment"
msgstr "Modification d’un rendez‑vous existant"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:79
msgid "To edit an existing appointment:"
msgstr "Pour modifier un rendez‑vous existant :"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:82 ../../appointments/toc.rst:93
msgid ""
"Right-click on the appointment you wish to edit, which is displayed on "
"your timetable."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez avec le bouton droit sur le rendez‑vous à modifier, affiché dans "
"votre emploi du temps."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:83 ../../appointments/toc.rst:119
#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:130 ../../appointments/toc.rst:141
#: ../../chat/toc.rst:80 ../../tasks/toc.rst:39
msgid "Select **Edit** from the drop-down menu."
msgstr "Sélectionnez **Edit** dans le menu déroulant."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:84 ../../appointments/toc.rst:120
msgid "Make changes."
msgstr "Apportez les modifications."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:85 ../../appointments/toc.rst:121
#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:132 ../../appointments/toc.rst:143
msgid ""
"If you have created the appointment solely for yourself, click **SAVE**. "
"If your appointment includes attendees, click **SEND** to notify them "
"about the changes via an automatic email."
msgstr ""
"Si vous avez créé le rendez‑vous uniquement pour vous, cliquez sur "
"**SAVE**. Si le rendez‑vous comporte des participants, cliquez sur "
"**SEND** pour les informer des changements par e‑mail automatique."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:88
msgid "Forwarding an Existing Appointment"
msgstr "Transfert d’un rendez‑vous existant"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:90
msgid "To forward an existing appointment:"
msgstr "Pour transférer un rendez‑vous existant :"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:94 ../../chat/toc.rst:109 ../../chat/toc.rst:117
msgid "Select **Forward** from the drop-down menu."
msgstr "Sélectionnez **Forward** dans le menu déroulant."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:95
msgid ""
"Enter the email address of the person you wish to forward the appointment"
" to."
msgstr "Saisissez l’adresse e‑mail du destinataire du transfert du rendez‑vous."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:96
msgid "Click **FORWARD** to send the appointment to the specified email address."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur **FORWARD** pour envoyer le rendez‑vous à l’adresse e‑mail "
"spécifiée."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:99
msgid "Canceling an Appointment"
msgstr "Annulation d’un rendez‑vous"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:101
msgid "To cancel an existing appointment:"
msgstr "Pour annuler un rendez‑vous existant :"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:104 ../../appointments/toc.rst:118
#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:129 ../../appointments/toc.rst:140
msgid "Right-click on the appointment displayed on your timetable."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez avec le bouton droit sur le rendez‑vous affiché dans votre emploi"
" du temps."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:105 ../../files/toc.rst:110
#: ../../tasks/toc.rst:50
msgid "Select **Delete** from the drop-down menu."
msgstr "Sélectionnez **Delete** dans le menu déroulant."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:106
msgid "Click the **SEND CANCELATION** or **DELETE** button to confirm."
msgstr "Cliquez sur le bouton **SEND CANCELATION** ou **DELETE** pour confirmer."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:108
msgid ""
"If there are attendees for this appointment, a notification email will "
"automatically be sent to the attendees to inform them about the "
"cancellation."
msgstr ""
"Si ce rendez‑vous comporte des participants, un e‑mail de notification "
"sera automatiquement envoyé aux participants pour les informer de "
"l’annulation."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:111
msgid "Moving an Existing Appointment to a Different Time"
msgstr "Déplacement d’un rendez‑vous existant vers une autre heure"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:113
msgid ""
"To reschedule an appointment to a different time, you can simply click "
"and hold on to the appointment in your timetable and drag it to another "
"time slot."
msgstr ""
"Pour reprogrammer un rendez‑vous à une autre heure, cliquez simplement "
"sur le rendez‑vous dans votre emploi du temps, maintenez le bouton "
"enfoncé et faites‑le glisser vers un autre créneau."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:115
msgid "Alternatively:"
msgstr "Alternative :"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:124
msgid "Adding / Removing Attendees to an Existing Appointment"
msgstr "Ajout / suppression de participants à un rendez‑vous existant"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:126
msgid "To add or remove attendees to an appointment:"
msgstr "Pour ajouter ou retirer des participants à un rendez‑vous :"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:131
msgid ""
"To add attendees, enter the email addresses of new attendees into the "
"**Attendees field**. To remove attendees, click the cross button next to "
"the attendees' email addresses."
msgstr ""
"Pour ajouter des participants, saisissez les adresses e‑mail des nouveaux"
" participants dans le **Attendees field**. Pour les retirer, cliquez sur "
"le bouton croix à côté des adresses e‑mail des participants."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:135
msgid "Adding a Meeting Room to an Existing Appointment"
msgstr "Ajout d’une salle de réunion à un rendez‑vous existant"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:137
msgid "To add a meeting room to an existing appointment:"
msgstr "Pour ajouter une salle de réunion à un rendez‑vous existant :"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:142
msgid ""
"Choose a meeting room from the available options in the **Meeting room "
"field**. Alternatively, if you prefer to host a virtual meeting using "
"|product| Chats' video meeting feature in one of your virtual rooms, you "
"can select the desired virtual room from the **Virtual Room field**."
msgstr ""
"Choisissez une salle de réunion parmi les options disponibles dans le "
"**Meeting room field**. Alternativement, si vous préférez organiser une "
"réunion virtuelle avec la fonction de visioconférence de |product| Chats "
"dans l’une de vos salles virtuelles, sélectionnez la salle virtuelle "
"souhaitée dans le **Virtual Room field**."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:145
msgid ""
"Please note that these meeting rooms are configured by your system "
"administrator. If you do not see the desired room listed, kindly contact "
"your system administrator to ensure all relevant meeting rooms in your "
"office are included. Similarly, if you have not set up any virtual rooms "
"yet, you can easily create them through the Chats section on the "
"|product| web client."
msgstr ""
"Veuillez noter que ces salles de réunion sont configurées par votre "
"administrateur système. Si la salle souhaitée n’apparaît pas, contactez "
"votre administrateur système afin que toutes les salles de réunion "
"pertinentes de votre bureau soient répertoriées. De même, si vous n’avez "
"pas encore créé de salles virtuelles, vous pouvez les créer facilement "
"via la section Chats du client web |product|."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:148
msgid "Creating a Recurring Appointment"
msgstr "Créer un rendez‑vous récurrent"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:150
msgid ""
"A recurring appointment is an event scheduled to occur repeatedly at "
"specified intervals, such as daily, weekly, monthly, or yearly. Rather "
"than creating separate appointments for each occurrence, a recurring "
"appointment allows you to set up a single event that repeats according to"
" your chosen pattern."
msgstr ""
"Un rendez‑vous récurrent est un événement programmé pour se répéter à des"
" intervalles spécifiés (quotidien, hebdomadaire, mensuel ou annuel). Au "
"lieu de créer des rendez‑vous distincts pour chaque occurrence, un "
"rendez‑vous récurrent vous permet de configurer un seul événement qui se "
"répète selon le modèle choisi."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:152
msgid "To create a recurring new appointment:"
msgstr "Pour créer un nouveau rendez‑vous récurrent :"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:156
msgid ""
"In the **From field**, select the identity you want to use to schedule "
"and send the appointment invitation."
msgstr ""
"Dans le **From field**, sélectionnez l’identité à utiliser pour planifier"
" et envoyer l’invitation au rendez‑vous."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:157
msgid "Enter a title for the appointment in the **Event title field**."
msgstr "Saisissez un titre pour le rendez‑vous dans le **Event title field**."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:159
msgid ""
"Choose a meeting room from the available options in the **Meeting room "
"field**. Please note that these meeting rooms are configured by your "
"system administrator. If you do not see the desired room listed, kindly "
"contact your system administrator to ensure all relevant meeting rooms in"
" your office are included."
msgstr ""
"Choisissez une salle de réunion parmi les options disponibles dans le "
"**Meeting room field**. Veuillez noter que ces salles sont configurées "
"par votre administrateur système. Si la salle souhaitée n’apparaît pas, "
"contactez votre administrateur système afin d’inclure toutes les salles "
"de réunion pertinentes de votre bureau."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:160
msgid ""
"Choose the required equipment from the available options under the "
"**Equipment field**. Please note that the equipment is configured by your"
" system administrator. If you do not see the desired equipment listed, "
"kindly contact your system administrator to ensure all relevant equipment"
" such as cameras, displays, etc. in your office are included."
msgstr ""
"Choisissez l’équipement requis parmi les options du champ **Equipment**. "
"L’équipement est configuré par votre administrateur système. Si "
"l’équipement souhaité n’apparaît pas, contactez votre administrateur pour"
" qu’il soit ajouté (caméras, écrans, etc.)."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:161
msgid ""
"If you prefer to host a virtual meeting using |product| Chats' video "
"meeting feature in one of your virtual rooms, you can select the desired "
"virtual room from the **Virtual Room field**. If you have not set up any "
"virtual rooms yet, you can easily create them through the Chats section "
"on the |product| web client."
msgstr ""
"Si vous préférez organiser une réunion virtuelle avec la fonction de "
"visioconférence de |product| Chats dans l’une de vos salles virtuelles, "
"sélectionnez la salle virtuelle souhaitée dans le **Virtual Room field**."
" Si vous n’avez pas encore configuré de salles virtuelles, vous pouvez "
"les créer facilement via la section Chats du client web |product|."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:166
msgid ""
"Choose the time slot for the appointment by specifying the start date and"
" time in the **Start date and time field**, and the end date and time in "
"the **End date and time field**. Alternatively, you can tick the checkbox"
" labeled All day if the appointment spans the entire day."
msgstr ""
"Choisissez le créneau horaire du rendez‑vous en indiquant la date et "
"l’heure de début dans le **Start date and time field**, et la date et "
"l’heure de fin dans le **End date and time field**. Vous pouvez également"
" cocher la case **All day** si le rendez‑vous dure toute la journée."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:169
msgid ""
"Choose your preferred option (Every Day, Every Week, Every Month, Every "
"Year) from the **Repeat field** to establish the recurring pattern."
msgstr ""
"Sélectionnez l’option souhaitée (Every Day, Every Week, Every Month, "
"Every Year) dans le **Repeat field** pour définir le schéma de "
"récurrence."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:173
msgid "Canceling a Recurring Appointment"
msgstr "Annuler un rendez‑vous récurrent"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:175
msgid "To cancel a recurring appointment:"
msgstr "Pour annuler un rendez‑vous récurrent :"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:178 ../../appointments/toc.rst:191
msgid ""
"Right-click on the appointment you wish to cancel, which is displayed on "
"your timetable."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez avec le bouton droit sur le rendez‑vous à annuler, affiché dans "
"votre emploi du temps."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:179
msgid "Go to the **Series** from the drop-down menu and select **Delete**."
msgstr ""
"Dans le menu déroulant, choisissez **Series** puis sélectionnez "
"**Delete**."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:180
msgid ""
"In this step, you can choose whether to delete all occurrences or only "
"this and future occurrences by selecting the appropriate option."
msgstr ""
"À cette étape, choisissez de supprimer toutes les occurrences ou "
"uniquement celle‑ci et les occurrences futures en sélectionnant l’option "
"appropriée."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:181 ../../appointments/toc.rst:193
msgid ""
"Click **DELETE** to confirm. If prompted, click **SEND CANCELATION** as "
"well."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur **DELETE** pour confirmer. Si une invite apparaît, cliquez "
"également sur **SEND CANCELATION**."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:183 ../../appointments/toc.rst:195
msgid ""
"If there are attendees for this appointment, a notification email will be"
" automatically sent to the attendees to inform them about the "
"cancellation."
msgstr ""
"Si des participants sont associés à ce rendez‑vous, un e‑mail de "
"notification sera automatiquement envoyé aux participants pour les "
"informer de l’annulation."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:186
msgid "Canceling a Single Instance of a Recurring Appointment"
msgstr "Annuler une occurrence unique d’un rendez‑vous récurrent"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:188
msgid "To cancel a single instance of a recurring appointment:"
msgstr "Pour annuler une occurrence unique d’un rendez‑vous récurrent :"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:192
msgid "Go to the **Instance** from the drop-down menu and select **Delete**."
msgstr ""
"Dans le menu déroulant, choisissez **Instance** puis sélectionnez "
"**Delete**."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:198
msgid "Responding to an Appointment Invitation"
msgstr "Répondre à une invitation de rendez‑vous"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:200
msgid ""
"When a colleague sends you an invitation for an appointment, you will "
"receive an automatic email indicating that you are invited. Inside the "
"email, you have four options to choose from:"
msgstr ""
"Lorsqu’un collègue vous envoie une invitation à un rendez‑vous, vous "
"recevez un e‑mail automatique indiquant que vous êtes invité. Dans "
"l’e‑mail, vous disposez de quatre options :"

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:203
msgid "**YES**: Confirm your attendance for the appointment."
msgstr "**YES** : Confirmer votre présence au rendez‑vous."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:204
msgid "**MAYBE**: Indicate that you are unsure about attending the appointment."
msgstr "**MAYBE** : Indiquer que votre présence est incertaine."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:205
msgid ""
"**NO**: Decline the invitation and indicate that you will not attend the "
"appointment."
msgstr ""
"**NO** : Refuser l’invitation et indiquer que vous n’assisterez pas au "
"rendez‑vous."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:206
msgid ""
"**PROPOSE NEW TIME**: Suggest an alternative time for the appointment if "
"the proposed time is not suitable for you."
msgstr ""
"**PROPOSE NEW TIME** : Proposer un autre créneau si le créneau proposé ne"
" vous convient pas."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:208
msgid ""
"Before selecting **YES**, you can also choose the calendar in which you "
"want to save the appointment from the Calendar field."
msgstr ""
"Avant de sélectionner **YES**, vous pouvez choisir le calendrier dans "
"lequel enregistrer le rendez‑vous dans le champ Calendar."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:210
msgid ""
"If you choose **PROPOSE NEW TIME**, a new window will appear where you "
"can select a new time slot for the appointment and then click the "
"**SEND** button."
msgstr ""
"Si vous choisissez **PROPOSE NEW TIME**, une nouvelle fenêtre s’affiche "
"où vous pouvez sélectionner un nouveau créneau puis cliquer sur le bouton"
" **SEND**."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:212
msgid ""
"Furthermore, you have the option to enable or disable the **Notify "
"organizer checkbox** based on whether you wish to send an automatic email"
" notification to them or not."
msgstr ""
"De plus, vous pouvez activer ou désactiver la case à cocher **Notify "
"organizer** selon que vous souhaitez envoyer ou non une notification "
"e‑mail automatique à l’organisateur."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:214
msgid ""
"After selecting one of the four buttons, the invitation email will "
"automatically be moved to your Trash folder."
msgstr ""
"Après avoir sélectionné l’un des quatre boutons, l’e‑mail d’invitation "
"est automatiquement déplacé vers votre dossier Corbeille."

#: ../../appointments/toc.rst:216
msgid ""
"If you don't choose any of the four options, the appointment will be "
"automatically saved in your calendar as a tentative appointment with an "
"icon indicating that you are not yet confirmed for the appointment. You "
"can later choose one of the four options by double-clicking on the "
"appointment in your calendar and selecting **Accept**, **Tentative**, "
"**Decline** or **Propose new time** from the drop-down menu. You can also"
" choose to **Delete** the appointment from your calendar without "
"responding to the invitation."
msgstr ""
"Si vous ne choisissez aucune des quatre options, le rendez‑vous est "
"enregistré automatiquement dans votre calendrier comme rendez‑vous "
"provisoire, avec une icône indiquant que vous n’êtes pas encore confirmé."
" Vous pouvez ensuite choisir une option en double‑cliquant sur le "
"rendez‑vous dans votre calendrier et en sélectionnant **Accept**, "
"**Tentative**, **Decline** ou **Propose new time** dans le menu "
"déroulant. Vous pouvez également **Delete** le rendez‑vous de votre "
"calendrier sans répondre à l’invitation."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:7
msgid "Basic Email Management"
msgstr "Gestion de base des e‑mails"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:9
msgid ""
"In this section, we will delve into the versatile functionalities of "
"|product|, focusing on its efficient organizational tools such as "
"folders, tags, and sharing capabilities."
msgstr ""
"Dans cette section, nous explorerons les fonctionnalités polyvalentes de "
"|product|, en nous concentrant sur ses outils d’organisation efficaces "
"tels que les dossiers, les tags et les possibilités de partage."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:12
msgid "Using Tags"
msgstr "Utilisation des tags"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:14
msgid ""
"Tags in |product| offer a versatile solution for classifying and "
"organizing emails. For instance, you might designate tags like \"Medium "
"Priority\" to swiftly categorize items according to their urgency or "
"importance."
msgstr ""
"Les tags dans |product| offrent une solution polyvalente pour classer et "
"organiser les e‑mails. Par exemple, vous pouvez créer des tags tels que «"
" Medium Priority » pour catégoriser rapidement les éléments selon leur "
"urgence ou importance."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:16
msgid ""
"Tags enable seamless organization, allowing users to easily locate items "
"associated with specific tags through efficient search functionality."
msgstr ""
"Les tags permettent une organisation fluide, offrant aux utilisateurs la "
"possibilité de localiser facilement les éléments associés à des tags "
"spécifiques grâce à une fonction de recherche efficace."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:18
msgid ""
"Moreover, the flexibility extends to the ability to apply multiple tags "
"to a single item, ensuring thorough categorization and enhanced "
"accessibility within the platform."
msgstr ""
"De plus, il est possible d’appliquer plusieurs tags à un même élément, "
"garantissant une catégorisation exhaustive et une accessibilité renforcée"
" sur la plateforme."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:20
msgid ""
"Your tags are located under the **Tags** section of the **Mails**. To "
"view your current tags:"
msgstr ""
"Vos tags se trouvent dans la section **Tags** des **Mails**. Pour "
"afficher vos tags actuels :"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:23
msgid "In the Navigation Panel of the mails section, locate the **Tags** section."
msgstr ""
"Dans le panneau de navigation de la section mails, repérez la section "
"**Tags**."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:24
msgid "Click on the downward arrow icon located next to the **Tags** section."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur l’icône de flèche vers le bas située à côté de la section "
"**Tags**."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:25
msgid "This action will expand or reveal your tags."
msgstr "Cette action développera ou affichera vos tags."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:32
msgid "Creating a Tag"
msgstr "Créer un tag"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:35
msgid "In the Navigation Panel of the mails section, locate the **Tags** option."
msgstr ""
"Dans le panneau de navigation de la section courriels, localisez l’option"
" **Tags**."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:36
msgid "Right-click on the Tags option."
msgstr "Cliquez avec le bouton droit sur l’option Tags."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:37
msgid "From the dropdown menu, select **Create Tag**."
msgstr "Dans le menu déroulant, choisissez **Create Tag**."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:38
msgid "A dialog box will appear. Insert a name for the new tag."
msgstr "Une boîte de dialogue apparaît. Saisissez un nom pour le nouveau tag."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:39
msgid "Choose a color for the tag from the options provided."
msgstr "Choisissez une couleur pour le tag parmi les options proposées."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:40
msgid "Click on the **CREATE** button to finalize the creation of the new tag."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur le bouton **CREATE** pour finaliser la création du nouveau "
"tag."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:43
msgid ""
"To see your tags, you should click on the downward arrow icon located "
"next to the Tags section."
msgstr ""
"Pour voir vos tags, cliquez sur l’icône flèche descendante située à côté "
"de la section Tags."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:47
msgid "Assigning a Tag to an Email"
msgstr "Attribuer un tag à un courriel"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:49
msgid "To assign a tag to an email simply:"
msgstr "Pour attribuer un tag à un courriel :"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:51
#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:75
msgid "Right-click on the email to open the dropdown menu."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez avec le bouton droit sur le courriel pour ouvrir le menu "
"déroulant."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:52
#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:76
msgid "Navigate to the Tags option within the dropdown menu."
msgstr "Accédez à l’option Tags dans le menu déroulant."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:53
msgid "Select one or multiple tags from the list."
msgstr "Sélectionnez un ou plusieurs tags dans la liste."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:60
msgid "Displaying Emails with a Specific Tag"
msgstr "Afficher les courriels avec un tag spécifique"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:62
msgid "To display emails with a specific tag:"
msgstr "Pour afficher les courriels avec un tag spécifique :"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:65
msgid "Locate the **Tags** section within the Navigation Panel."
msgstr "Localisez la section **Tags** dans le panneau de navigation."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:66
msgid ""
"Click on the downward arrow icon located next to the Tags section to open"
" the list of tags."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez sur l’icône flèche descendante située à côté de la section Tags "
"pour ouvrir la liste des tags."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:67
msgid "Click on the tag that you want to find emails for."
msgstr "Cliquez sur le tag dont vous souhaitez afficher les courriels."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:68
msgid "All messages with the selected tag will be displayed in the Main Panel."
msgstr ""
"Tous les messages avec le tag sélectionné s’affichent dans le panneau "
"principal."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:71
msgid "Removing a Tag from an Email"
msgstr "Supprimer un tag d’un courriel"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:73
msgid "To remove a tag from an email simply:"
msgstr "Pour supprimer une étiquette d’un e‑mail, procédez ainsi :"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:77
msgid "Uncheck one or multiple tags from the list."
msgstr "Décochez une ou plusieurs étiquettes dans la liste."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:80
msgid "Changing a Tag Color"
msgstr "Modifier la couleur d’une étiquette"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:82
msgid "Right-click on the tag you need to edit from the Tags section."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez avec le bouton droit sur l’étiquette à modifier dans la section "
"Tags."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:83
msgid "From the dropdown menu, select Edit Tag."
msgstr "Dans le menu déroulant, choisissez « Edit Tag »."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:84
msgid ""
"A dialog box will appear. Choose a color for the tag from the options "
"provided."
msgstr ""
"Une boîte de dialogue s’affiche. Sélectionnez une couleur pour "
"l’étiquette parmi les options proposées."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:85
msgid "Click on the EDIT button."
msgstr "Cliquez sur le bouton EDIT."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:88
msgid "Renaming a Tag"
msgstr "Renommer une étiquette"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:90
msgid "Right-click on the tag you need to edit from the **Tags** section."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez avec le bouton droit sur l’étiquette à modifier dans la section "
"**Tags**."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:91
msgid "From the dropdown menu, select **Edit Tag**."
msgstr "Dans le menu déroulant, choisissez **Edit Tag**."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:92
msgid "A dialog box will appear. Edit the name."
msgstr "Une boîte de dialogue s’affiche. Modifiez le nom."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:93
msgid "Click on the **EDIT** button."
msgstr "Cliquez sur le bouton **EDIT**."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:96
msgid "Deleting a Tag"
msgstr "Supprimer une étiquette"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:98
msgid "Right-click on the tag you need to delete from the **Tags** section."
msgstr ""
"Cliquez avec le bouton droit sur l’étiquette à supprimer dans la section "
"**Tags**."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:99
msgid "From the dropdown menu, select **Delete Tag**."
msgstr "Dans le menu déroulant, choisissez **Delete Tag**."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:102
msgid "Marking an Email with a Flag"
msgstr "Marquer un e‑mail avec un drapeau"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:104
msgid ""
"A flag acts like a special tag for important emails, showing up with a "
"red flag icon next to the subject line."
msgstr ""
"Un drapeau fonctionne comme une étiquette spéciale pour les e‑mails "
"importants, affiché avec une icône de drapeau rouge à côté de l’objet."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:106
msgid ""
"Flagging emails is handy for various reasons. For instance, it helps you "
"quickly find important emails you will need to refer to later. It is also"
" useful for highlighting specific emails in shared folders so your "
"colleagues can easily find them."
msgstr ""
"Le marquage d’e‑mails est pratique pour plusieurs raisons : il vous "
"permet de retrouver rapidement les e‑mails importants à consulter "
"ultérieurement et facilite la mise en évidence d’e‑mails spécifiques dans"
" les dossiers partagés pour que vos collègues les trouvent aisément."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:108
msgid "To mark an email with a flag, simply:"
msgstr "Pour marquer un e‑mail avec un drapeau, procédez ainsi :"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:111
msgid "From the dropdown menu select **Add Flag**."
msgstr "Dans le menu déroulant, choisissez **Add Flag**."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:112
msgid ""
"Your email will have a red flag displayed on the right side of the "
"subject line."
msgstr "Votre e‑mail affichera un drapeau rouge à droite de la ligne d’objet."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:119
msgid "Removing Flag from an Email"
msgstr "Suppression du drapeau d’un e‑mail"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:121
msgid "To remove the flag from an email, simply:"
msgstr "Pour supprimer le drapeau d’un e‑mail, procédez ainsi :"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:124
msgid "From the dropdown menu select **Remove Flag**."
msgstr "Dans le menu déroulant, choisissez **Supprimer le drapeau**."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:128
msgid "Using Folders"
msgstr "Utilisation des dossiers"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:130
msgid ""
"Folders serve to arrange both incoming and outgoing email correspondence."
" You have the option to create your folders or utilize predefined system "
"folders:"
msgstr ""
"Les dossiers permettent d’organiser le courrier entrant et sortant. Vous "
"pouvez créer vos dossiers ou utiliser les dossiers système prédéfinis :"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:132
msgid ""
"**System folders** - These folders are immutable; they cannot be "
"relocated, renamed, or erased. The system includes the following folders:"
msgstr ""
"**Dossiers système** – Ces dossiers sont immuables ; ils ne peuvent être "
"déplacés, renommés ou supprimés. Le système comprend les dossiers "
"suivants :"

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:134
msgid "**Inbox**: The primary destination for new incoming email messages."
msgstr ""
"**Boîte de réception** : destination principale des nouveaux messages "
"entrants."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:135
msgid "**Sent**: Contains a copy of all outgoing emails."
msgstr "**Éléments envoyés** : contient une copie de tous les e‑mails sortants."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:136
msgid "**Drafts**: Emails you have composed but not yet sent."
msgstr "**Brouillons** : e‑mails que vous avez rédigés mais pas encore envoyés."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:137
msgid ""
"**Junk**: Incoming emails suspected to be spam or junk, although not "
"definitively, are directed here. You can sift through these messages, "
"moving or deleting them as necessary. If left untouched, they are "
"automatically purged according to the administrator's settings."
msgstr ""
"**Indésirables** : les e‑mails entrants suspectés d’être du spam y sont "
"dirigés. Vous pouvez les trier, les déplacer ou les supprimer selon vos "
"besoins. S’ils ne sont pas traités, ils sont automatiquement purgés selon"
" les paramètres de l’administrateur."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:138
msgid ""
"**Trash**: Deleted items are relocated here and remain until you manually"
" empty the trash or until automated purging occurs."
msgstr ""
"**Corbeille** : les éléments supprimés sont déplacés ici et y restent "
"jusqu’à ce que vous vidiez manuellement la corbeille ou qu’une purge "
"automatisée s’exécute."

#: ../../basic_email_management/toc.rst:140
msgid ""
"**User-defined folders**: These folders, which you create to structure "
"your email, appear in the Folder list within the Overview pane. It is "
"important to note that top-level folder names must be unique and cannot "
"match any other top-level folder within your inbox."
msgstr ""
"**Dossiers personnalisés** : ces dossiers que vous créez pour structurer "
"votre messagerie apparaissent dans la liste des dossiers du volet "
"d’aperçu. Les noms des dossiers de niveau supérieur doivent être uniques "
"et ne pas correspondre à un autre dossier de même niveau dans votre boîte"
" de réception."

